obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (11153)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11153&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Electricity Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words except the State of Jammu and Kashmir omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 10th June, 2003 (ss. 1 to 120 and ss. 122 to 185), vide notification No. S.O. 669(E), dated 10th June, 2003, see Gazette of`
  line `India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (11154)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11154&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1)"Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal for Electricity established under section 110;`
  line
  line `(2) "appointed date" means such date as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line
  line `(3) "area of supply" means the area within which a distribution licensee is authorised by his licence to`
  line `supply electricity;`
  line
  line `(4) "Appropriate Commission" means the Central Regulatory Commission referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 76 or the State Regulatory Commission referred to in section 82 or the Joint`
  line `Commission referred to in section 83, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(5) "Appropriate Government" means,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government,--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of a generating company wholly or partly owned by it;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any inter-State generation, transmission, trading or supply of electricity`
  line `and with respect to any mines, oil-fields, railways, national highways, airports, telegraphs,`
  line `broadcasting stations and any works of defence, dockyard, nuclear power installations;`
  line
  line `(iii) in respect of National Load Despatch Centre and Regional Load Despatch Centre;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to any works or electric installation belonging to it or under its control;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the State Government, having jurisdiction under this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) "Authority" mean the Central Electricity Authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(7) "Board" means a State Electricity Board, constituted before the commencement of this Act, under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(8) "Captive generating plant" means a power plant set up by any person to generate electricity`
  line `primarily for his own use and includes a power plant set up by any co-operative society or association of`
  line `persons for generating electricity primarily for use of members of such co-operative society or`
  line association;
  line
  line `(9) "Central Commission" means the Central Electricity Regulatory Commission referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 76;`
  line
  line `(10) "Central Transmission Utility" means any Government company which the Central Government`
  line `may notify under sub-section (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(11) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Authority or Appropriate Commission or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(12) "Cogeneration" means a process which simultaneously produces two or more forms of useful`
  line `energy (including electricity);`
  line
  line `(13) "company" means a company formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)`
  line `and includes any body corporate under a Central, State or Provincial Act;`
  line
  line `(14) "conservation" means any reduction in consumption of electricity as a result of increase in the`
  line `efficiency in supply and use of electricity;`
  line
  line `(15) "consumer" means any person who is supplied with electricity for his own use by a licensee or`
  line `the Government or by any other person engaged in the business of supplying electricity to the public`
  line `under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and includes any person whose premises are for`
  line `the time being connected for the purpose of receiving electricity with the works of a licensee, the`
  line `Government or such other person, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(16) "dedicated transmission lines" means any electric supply-line for point to point transmission`
  line `which are required for the purpose of connecting electric lines or electric plants of a captive generating`
  line `plant referred to in section 9 or generating station referred to in section 10 to any transmission lines or`
  line `sub-stations, or generating stations, or the load centre, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(17) "distribution licensee" means a licensee authorised to operate and maintain a distribution system`
  line `for supplying electricity to the consumers in his area of supply;`
  line
  line `(18) "distributing main" means the portion of any main with which a service line is, or is intended to`
  line `be, immediately connected;`
  line
  line `(19) "distribution system" means the system of wires and associated facilities between the delivery`
  line `points on the transmission lines or the generating station connection and the point of connection to the`
  line `installation of the consumers;`
  line
  line `(20) "electric line" means any line which is used for carrying electricity for any purpose and`
  line includes--
  line
  line `(a) any support for any such line, that is to say, any structure, tower, pole or other thing in, on, by`
  line `or from which any such line is, or may be, supported, carried or suspended; and`
  line
  line `(b) any apparatus connected to any such line for the purpose of carrying electricity;`
  line
  line `(21) "Electrical Inspector" means a person appointed as such by the Appropriate Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 162 and also includes Chief Electrical Inspector;`
  line
  line `(22) "electrical plant" means any plant, equipment, apparatus or appliance or any part thereof used`
  line `for, or connected with, the generation, transmission, distribution or supply of electricity but does not`
  line include--
  line
  line `(a) an electric line; or`
  line
  line `(b) a meter used for ascertaining the quantity of electricity supplied to any premises; or`
  line
  line `(c) an electrical equipment, apparatus or appliance under the control of a consumer;`
  line
  line `(23) "electricity" means electrical energy--`
  line
  line `(a) generated, transmitted, supplied or traded for any purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) used for any purpose except the transmission of a message;`
  line
  line `(24) "Electricity Supply Code" means the Electricity Supply Code specified under section 50;`
  line
  line `(25) "electricity system" means a system under the control of a generating company or licensee, as`
  line `the case may be, having one or more--`
  line
  line `(a) generating stations; or`
  line
  line `(b) transmission lines; or`
  line
  line `(c) electric lines and sub-stations,`
  line
  line `and when used in the context of a State or the Union, the entire electricity system within the territories`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(26) "electricity trader" means a person who has been granted a licence to undertake trading in`
  line `electricity under section 12;`
  line
  line `(27) "franchisee" means a persons authorised by a distribution licensee to distribute electricity on its`
  line `behalf in a particular area within his area of supply;`
  line
  line `(28) "generating company" means any company or body corporate or association or body of`
  line `individuals, whether incorporated or not, or artificial juridical person, which owns or operates or`
  line `maintains a generating station;`
  line
  line `(29) "generate" means to produce electricity from a generating station for the purpose of giving`
  line `supply to any premises or enabling a supply to be so given;`
  line
  line `(30) "generating station" or "station" means any station for generating electricity, including any`
  line `building and plant with step-up transformer, switch-gear, switch yard, cables or other appurtenant`
  line `equipment, if any, used for that purpose and the site thereof; a site intended to be used for a generating`
  line `station, and any building used for housing the operating staff of a generating station, and where electricity`
  line `is generated by water-power, includes penstocks, head and tail works, main and regulating reservoirs,`
  line `dams and other hydraulic works, but does not in any case include any sub-station;`
  line
  line `(31) "Government company" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 617 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(32) "grid" means the high voltage backbone system of inter-connected transmission lines,`
  line `sub-station and generating plants;`
  line
  line `(33) "Grid Code" means the Grid Code specified by the Central Commission under clause (h) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(34) "Grid Standards" means the Grid Standards specified under clause (d) of section 73 by the`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(35) "high voltage line" means an electric line or cable of a nominal voltage as may be specified by`
  line `the Authority from time to time;`
  line
  line `(36) "inter-State transmission system" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any system for the conveyance of electricity by means of main transmission line from the`
  line `territory of one State to another State;`
  line
  line `(ii) the conveyance of electricity across the territory of an intervening State as well as conveyance`
  line `within the State which is incidental to such inter-State transmission of electricity;`
  line
  line `(iii) the transmission of electricity within the territory of a State on a system built, owned,`
  line `operated, maintained or controlled by a Central Transmission Utility;`
  line
  line `(37) 'intra-State transmission system' means any system for transmission of electricity other than an`
  line `inter-State transmission system;`
  line
  line `(38) 'licence" means a licence granted under section 14;`
  line
  line `(39) "licensee" means a person who has been granted a licence under section 14;`
  line
  line `(40) "line" means any wire, cable, tube, pipe, insulator, conductor or other similar thing (including its`
  line `casing or coating) which is designed or adapted for use in carrying electricity and includes any line which`
  line `surrounds or supports, or is surrounded or supported by or is installed in close proximity to, or is`
  line `supported, carried or suspended in association with, any such line;`
  line
  line `(41) "local authority" means any Nagar Panchayat, Municipal Council, municipal corporation,`
  line `Panchayat constituted at the village, intermediate and district levels, body of port commissioners or other`
  line `authority legally entitled to, or entrusted by the Union or any State Government with, the control or`
  line `management of any area or local fund;`
  line
  line `(42) "main" means any electric supply-line through which electricity is, or is intended to be,`
  line supplied;
  line
  line `(43) "Member" means the Member of the Appropriate Commission or Authority or Joint`
  line `Commission, or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, and includes the Chairperson of such`
  line `Commission or Authority or Appellate Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(44) "National Electricity Plan" means the National Electricity Plan notified under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(45) "National Load Despatch Centre" means the Centre established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(46) "notification" means notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression "notify"`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(47) "open access" means the non-discriminatory provision for the use of transmission lines or`
  line `distribution system or associated facilities with such lines or system by any licensee or consumer or a`
  line `person engaged in generation in accordance with the regulations specified by the Appropriate`
  line Commission;
  line
  line `(48) "overhead line" means an electric line which is placed above the ground and in the open air but`
  line `does not include live rails of a traction system;`
  line
  line `(49) "person" shall include any company or body corporate or association or body of individuals,`
  line `whether incorporated or not, or artificial juridical person;`
  line
  line `(50) "power system" means all aspects of generation, transmission, distribution and supply of`
  line `electricity and includes one or more of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) generating stations;`
  line
  line `(b) transmission or main transmission lines;`
  line
  line `(c) sub-stations;`
  line
  line `(d) tie-lines;`
  line
  line `(e) load despatch activities;`
  line
  line `(f) mains or distribution mains;`
  line
  line `(g) electric supply-lines;`
  line
  line `(h) overhead lines;`
  line
  line `(i) service lines;`
  line
  line `(j) works;`
  line
  line `(51) "premises" includes any land, building or structure;`
  line
  line `(52) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Appropriate Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(53) "public lamp" means an electric lamp used for the lighting of any street;`
  line
  line `(54) "real time operation" means action to be taken at a given time at which information about the`
  line `electricity system is made available to the concerned Load Despatch Centre;`
  line
  line `(55) "Regional Power Committee" means a committee established by resolution by the Central`
  line `Government for a specified region for facilitating the integrated operation of the power systems in that`
  line region;
  line
  line `(56) "Regional Load Despatch Centre" means the Centre established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(57) "regulations" means regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(58) "repealed laws" means the Indian Electricity Act, 1910 (9 of 1910), the Electricity (Supply) Act,`
  line `1948 (54 of 1948) and the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) repealed by`
  line `section 185;`
  line
  line `(59) "rules" means rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(60) "Schedule" means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(61) "service-line" means any electric supply-line through which electricity is, or is intended to be,`
  line supplied--
  line
  line `(a) to a single consumer either from a distributing main or immediately from the Distribution`
  line `Licensee's premises; or`
  line
  line `(b) from a distributing main to a group of consumers on the same premises or on contiguous`
  line `premises supplied from the same point of the distributing main;`
  line
  line `(62) 'specified" means specified by regulations made by the Appropriate Commission or the`
  line `Authority, as the case may be, under this Act;`
  line
  line `(63) "stand alone system" means the electricity system set-up to generate power and distribute`
  line `electricity in a specified area without connection to the grid;`
  line
  line `(64) "State Commission" means the State Electricity Regulatory Commission constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 82 and includes a Joint Commission constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 83;`
  line
  line `(65) "State Grid Code" means the State Grid Code specified under clause (h) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 86;`
  line
  line `(66) "State Load Despatch Centre" means the centre established under sub-section (1) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(67) "State Transmission Utility" means the Board or the Government company specified as such by`
  line `the State Government under sub-section (1) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(68) "street" includes any way, road, lane, square, court, alley, passage or open space, whether a`
  line `thoroughfare or not, over which the public have a right of way, and also the roadway and footway over`
  line `any public bridge or causeway;`
  line
  line `(69) "sub-station" means a station for transforming or converting electricity for the transmission or`
  line `distribution thereof and includes transformers converters, switch-gears, capacitors, synchronous`
  line `condensers, structures, cable and other appurtenant equipment and any buildings used for that purpose`
  line `and the site thereof;`
  line
  line `(70) "supply", in relation to electricity, means the sale of electricity to a licensee or consumer;`
  line
  line `(71) "trading" means purchase of electricity for resale thereof and the expression "trade" shall be`
  line `construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(72) "transmission lines means all high pressure cables and overhead lines (not being an essential`
  line `part of the distribution system of a licensee) transmitting electricity from a generating station to another`
  line `generating station or a sub-station, together with any step-up and step-down transformers, switch-gear and`
  line `other works necessary to and used for the control of such cables or overhead lines, and such buildings or`
  line `part thereof as may be required to accommodate such transformers, switch-gear and other works;`
  line
  line `(73) "transmission licensee" means a licensee authorised to establish or operate transmission lines;`
  line
  line `(74) "transmit" means conveyance of electricity by means of transmission lines and the expression`
  line `"transmission" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(75) "utility" means the electric lines or electrical plant, and includes all lands, buildings, works and`
  line `materials attached thereto belonging to any person acting as a generating company or licensee under the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(76) "wheeling" means the operation whereby the distribution system and associated facilities of a`
  line `transmission licensee or distribution licensee, as the case may be, are used by another person for the`
  line `conveyance of electricity on payment of charges to be determined under section 62;`
  line
  line `(77) "works" includes electric line, and any building, plant, machinery, apparatus and any other thing`
  line `of whatever description required to transmit, distribute or supply electricity to the public and to carry into`
  line `effect the objects of a licence or sanction granted under this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (11155)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `National Electricity Policy and Plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11155&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, from time to time,`
  line `prepare the National Electricity Policy and tariff policy, in consultation with the State Governments and`
  line `the Authority for development of the power system based on optimal utilisation of resources such as coal,`
  line `natural gas, nuclear substances or materials, hydro and renewable sources of energy.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall publish National Electricity Policy and tariff policy from time to`
  line time.
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, from time to time, in consultation with the State Governments and`
  line `the Authority, review or revise, the National Electricity Policy and tariff policy referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall prepare a National Electricity Plan in accordance with the National Electricity`
  line `Policy and notify such plan once in five years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority while preparing the National Electricity Plan shall publish the draft`
  line `National Electricity Plan and invite suggestions and objections thereon from licensees, generating`
  line `companies and the public within such time as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority shall-`
  line
  line `(a) notify the plan after obtaining the approval of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) revise the plan incorporating therein the directions, if any, given by the Central Government`
  line `while granting approval under clause (a).`
  line
  line `(5) The Authority may review or revise the National Electricity Plan in accordance with the National`
  line `Electricity Policy.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (11156)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `National policy on stand alone systems for rural areas and non-conventional energy systems.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11156&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, after consultation with the State Governments, prepare and notify a`
  line `national policy, permitting stand alone systems (including those based on renewable sources of energy`
  line `and other non-conventional sources of energy) for rural areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (11157)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `National policy on electrification and local distribution in rural areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11157&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government shall also formulate a national policy, in consultation with the State Governments and the`
  line `State Commissions, for rural electrification and for bulk purchase of power and management of local`
  line `distribution in rural areas through Panchayat Institutions, users associations, co-operative societies,`
  line `non-Governmental organisations or franchisees.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (11158)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Joint responsibility of State Government and Central Government in rural electrification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 2, for section 6 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11158&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[6. Joint responsibility of State Government and Central Government in rural electrification.–The concerned State Government and the Central Government shall jointly endeavour to provide access`
  line `to electricity to all areas including villages and hamlets through rural electricity infrastructure and`
  line `electrification of households.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (11159)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Generating company and requirement for setting up of generating station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11159&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Any generating`
  line `company may establish, operate and maintain a generating station without obtaining a licence under this`
  line `Act if it complies with the technical standards relating to connectivity with the grid referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of section 73.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (11160)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Hydro-electric generation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11160&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, any generating`
  line `company intending to set up a hydro-generating station shall prepare and submit to the Authority for its`
  line `concurrence, a scheme estimated to involve a capital expenditure exceeding such sum, as may be fixed by`
  line `the Central Government, from time to time, by notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall, before concurring in any scheme submitted to it under sub-section (1) have`
  line `particular regard to, whether or not in its opinion,--`
  line
  line `(a) the proposed river-works will prejudice the prospects for the best ultimate development of the`
  line `river or its tributaries for power generation, consistent with the requirements of drinking water,irrigation, navigation, flood-control, or other public purposes, and for this purpose the Authority shall`
  line `satisfy itself, after consultation with the State Government, the Central Government, or such other`
  line `agencies as it may deem appropriate, that an adequate study has been made of the optimum location`
  line `of dams and other river-works;`
  line
  line `(b) the proposed scheme meets the norms regarding dam design and safety.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a multi-purpose scheme for the development of any river in any region is in operation, the`
  line `State Government and the generating company shall co-ordinate their activities with the activities of the`
  line `persons responsible for such scheme in so far as they are inter-related.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (11161)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Captive generation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11161&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, a person may construct,`
  line `maintain or operate a captive generating plant and dedicated transmission lines:`
  line
  line `Provided that the supply of electricity from the captive generating plant through the grid shall be`
  line `regulated in the same manner as the generating station of a generating company:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided further that no licence shall be required under this Act for supply of electricity generated`
  line `from a captive generating plant to any licensee in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules`
  line `and regulations made thereunder and to any consumer subject to the regulations made under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 42.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every person, who has constructed a captive generating plant and maintains and operates such`
  line `plant, shall have the right to open access for the purposes of carrying electricity from his captive`
  line `generating plant to the destination of his use:`
  line
  line `Provided that such open access shall be subject to availability of adequate transmission facility and`
  line `such availability of transmission facility shall be determined by the Central Transmission Utility or the`
  line `State Transmission Utility, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any dispute regarding the availability of transmission facility shall be`
  line `adjudicated upon by the Appropriate Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (11162)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duties of generating companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11162&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the duties of a`
  line `generating company shall be to establish, operate and maintain generating stations, tie-lines, sub-stations`
  line `and dedicated transmission lines connected therewith in accordance with the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) A generating company may supply electricity to any licensee in accordance with this Act and the`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder and may, subject to the regulations made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 42, supply electricity to any consumer.`
  line
  line `(3) Every generating company shall--`
  line
  line `(a) submit technical details regarding its generating stations to the Appropriate Commission and`
  line `the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) co-ordinate with the Central Transmission Utility or the State Transmission Utility, as the case`
  line `may be, for transmission of the electricity generated by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (11163)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Directions to generating companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11163&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Government may specify that a`
  line `generating company shall, in extraordinary circumstances operate and maintain any generating station in`
  line `accordance with the directions of that Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "extraordinary circumstances" means`
  line `circumstances arising out of threat to security of the State, public order or a natural calamity or such other`
  line `circumstances arising in the public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Commission may offset the adverse financial impact of the directions referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) on any generating company in such manner as it considers appropriate.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (11164)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Authorised persons to transmit, supply, etc., electricity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11164&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) transmit electricity; or`
  line
  line `(b) distribute electricity; or`
  line
  line `(c) undertake trading in electricity,`
  line
  line `unless he is authorised to do so by a licence issued under section 14, or is exempt under section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (11165)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11165&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may, on the recommendations of the`
  line `Appropriate Government, in accordance with the national policy formulated under section 5 and in the`
  line `public interest, direct, by notification that subject to such conditions and restrictions, if any, and for such`
  line `period or periods, as may be specified in the notification, the provisions of section 12 shall not apply to`
  line `any local authority, Panchayat Institution, users association, co-operative societies, non-governmental`
  line `organisations, or franchisees.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (11166)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Grant of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 2, for "(including the capital adequacy, creditworthiness, or code of conduct)" (w.e.f. 27-1-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11166&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may, on an application made to it under section`
  line `15, grant a licence to any person--`
  line
  line `(a) to transmit electricity as a transmission licensee; or`
  line
  line `(b) to distribute electricity as a distribution licensee; or`
  line
  line `(c) to undertake trading in electricity as an electricity trader,`
  line
  line `in any area as may be specified in the licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person engaged in the business of transmission or supply of electricity under the`
  line `provisions of the repealed laws or any Act specified in the Schedule on or before the appointed date shall`
  line `be deemed to be a licensee under this Act for such period as may be stipulated in the licence, clearance or`
  line `approval granted to him under the repealed laws or such Act specified in the Schedule, and the provisions`
  line `of the repealed laws or such Act specified in the Schedule in respect of such licence shall apply for a`
  line `period of one year from the date of commencement of this Act or such earlier period as may be specified,`
  line `at the request of the licensee, by the Appropriate Commission and thereafter the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall apply to such business:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Transmission Utility or the State Transmission Utility shall be`
  line `deemed to be a transmission licensee under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case an Appropriate Government transmits electricity or distributes electricity or`
  line `undertakes trading in electricity, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, such Government`
  line `shall be deemed to be a licensee under this Act, but shall not be required to obtain a licence under this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Damodar Valley Corporation, established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of`
  line `the Damodar Valley Corporation Act, 1948 (14 of 1948), shall be deemed to be a licensee under this Act`
  line `but shall not be required to obtain a licence under this Act and the provisions of the Damodar ValleyCorporation Act, 1948 (14 of 1948), in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `shall continue to apply to that Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Government company or the company referred to in sub-section (2) of section`
  line `131 of this Act and the company or companies created in pursuance of the Acts specified in the Schedule,`
  line `shall be deemed to be a licensee under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Appropriate Commission may grant a licence to two or more persons for`
  line `distribution of electricity through their own distribution system within the same area, subject to the`
  line `conditions that the applicant for grant of licence within the same area shall, without prejudice to the other`
  line `conditions or requirements under this Act, comply with the additional requirements^1`
  line `[relating to the`
  line `capital adequacy, creditworthiness, or code of conduct] as may be prescribed by the Central Government,`
  line `and no such applicant, who complies with all the requirements for grant of licence, shall be refused grant`
  line `of licence on the ground that there already exists a licensee in the same area for the same purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in a case where a distribution licensee proposes to undertake distribution of`
  line `electricity for a specified area within his area of supply through another person, that person shall not be`
  line `required to obtain any separate licence from the concerned State Commission and such distribution.`
  line `licensee shall be responsible for distribution of electricity in his area of supply:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where a person intends to generate and distribute electricity in a rural area to be`
  line `notified by the State Government, such person shall not require any licence for such generation and`
  line `distribution of electricity, but he shall comply with the measures which may be specified by the Authority`
  line `under section 53:`
  line
  line `Provided also that a distribution licensee shall not require a licence to undertake trading in electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (11167)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Procedure for grant of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11167&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application under section 14 shall be made in such`
  line `form and in such manner as may be specified by the Appropriate Commission and shall be accompanied`
  line `by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who has made an application for grant of licence shall, within seven days after`
  line `making such application, publish a notice of his application with such particulars and in such manner as`
  line `may be specified and a licence shall not be granted`
  line
  line `(i) until the objections, if any, received by the Appropriate Commission in response to publication`
  line `of the application have been considered by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that no objection shall be so considered unless it is received before the expiration of`
  line `thirty days from the date of the publication of the notice as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(ii) until, in the case of an application for a licence for an area including the whole or any part of`
  line `any cantonment, aerodrome, fortress, arsenal, dockyard or camp or of any building or place in the`
  line `occupation of the Government for defence purposes, the Appropriate Commission has ascertained`
  line `that there is no objection to the grant of the licence on the part of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A person intending to act as a transmission licensee shall, immediately on making the application,`
  line `forward a copy of such application to the Central Transmission Utility or the State Transmission Utility,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Transmission Utility or the State Transmission Utility, as the case may be, shall,`
  line `within thirty days after the receipt of the copy of the application referred to in sub-section (3), send its`
  line `recommendations, if any, to the Appropriate Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that such recommendations shall not be binding on the Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) Before granting a licence under section 14, the Appropriate Commission shall--`
  line
  line `(a) publish a notice in two such daily newspapers, as that Commission may consider necessary,`
  line `stating the name and address of the person to whom it proposes to issue the licence;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all suggestions or objections and the recommendations, if any, of the Central`
  line `Transmission Utility or State Transmission Utility, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a person makes an application under sub-section (1) of section 14 to act as a licensee,`
  line `the Appropriate Commission shall, as far as practicable, within ninety days after receipt of such`
  line application,--
  line
  line `(a) issue a licence subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application for reasons to be recorded in writing if such application does not`
  line `conform to the provisions of this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder or the`
  line `provisions of any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given an opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(7) The Appropriate Commission shall, immediately after issue of a licence, forward a copy of the`
  line `licence to the Appropriate Government, Authority, local authority, and to such other person as the`
  line `Appropriate Commission considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(8) A licence shall continue to be in force for a period of twenty-five years unless such licence is`
  line revoked.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (11168)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Conditions of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11168&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may specify any general or specific`
  line `conditions which shall apply either to a licensee or class of licensees and such conditions shall be deemed`
  line `to be conditions of such licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appropriate Commission shall, within one year from the appointed date, specify`
  line `any general or specific conditions of licence applicable to the licensees referred to in the first, second,`
  line `third, fourth and fifth provisos to section 14 after the expiry of one year from the commencement of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (11169)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Licensee not to do certain things.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11169&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No licensee shall, without prior approval of the`
  line `Appropriate Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) undertake any transaction to acquire by purchase or takeover or otherwise, the utility of any`
  line `other licensee; or`
  line
  line `(b) merge his utility with the utility of any other licensee:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply if the utility of the licensee is situate in`
  line `a State other than the State in which the utility referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) is situate.`
  line
  line `(2) Every licensee shall, before obtaining the approval under sub-section (1), give not less than one`
  line `month's notice to every other licensee who transmits or distributes, electricity in the area of such licensee`
  line `who applies for such approval.`
  line
  line `(3) No licensee shall at any time assign his licence or transfer his utility, or any part thereof, by sale,`
  line `lease, exchange or otherwise without the prior approval of the Appropriate Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) Any agreement, relating to any transaction specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), unless`
  line `made with the prior approval of the Appropriate Commission, shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (11170)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Amendment of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11170&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in its opinion the public interest so permits, the Appropriate`
  line `Commission, may, on the application of the licensee or otherwise, make such alterations and amendments`
  line `in the terms and conditions of his licence as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such alterations or amendments shall be made except with the consent of the`
  line `licensee unless such consent has, in the opinion of the Appropriate Commission, been unreasonably`
  line withheld.
  line
  line `(2) Before any alterations or amendments in the licence are made under this section, the following`
  line `provisions shall have effect, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the licensee has made an application under sub-section (1) proposing any alteration or`
  line `modifications in his licence, the licensee shall publish a notice of such application with such`
  line `particulars and in such manner as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an application proposing alterations or modifications in the area of supply`
  line `comprising the whole or any part of any cantonment, aerodrome, fortress, arsenal, dockyard or camp`
  line `or any building or place in the occupation of the Government for defence purposes, the Appropriate`
  line `Commission shall not make any alterations or modifications except with the consent of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) where any alterations or modifications in a licence are proposed to be made otherwise than on`
  line `the application of the licensee, the Appropriate Commission shall publish the proposed alterations or`
  line `modifications with such particulars and in such manner as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(d) the Appropriate Commission shall not make any alterations or modifications unless all`
  line `suggestions or objections received within thirty days from the date of the first publication of the`
  line `notice have been considered.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (11171)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Revocation of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11171&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Appropriate Commission, after making an enquiry, is satisfied`
  line `that public interest so requires, it may revoke a licence in any of the following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the licensee, in the opinion of the Appropriate Commission, makes wilful and`
  line `prolonged default in doing anything required of him by or under this Act or the rules or regulations`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) where the licensee breaks any of the terms or conditions of his licence the breach of which is`
  line `expressly declared by such licence to render it liable to revocation;`
  line
  line `(c) where the licensee fails, within the period fixed in this behalf by his licence, or any longer`
  line `period which the Appropriate Commission may have granted therefor--`
  line
  line `(i) to show, to the satisfaction of the Appropriate Commission, that he is in a position fully`
  line `and efficiently to discharge the duties and obligations imposed on him by his licence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to make the deposit or furnish the security, or pay the fees or other charges required by his`
  line licence;
  line
  line `(d) where in the opinion of the Appropriate Commission the financial position of the licensee is`
  line `such that he is unable fully and efficiently to discharge the duties and obligations imposed on him by`
  line `his licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in its opinion the public interest so requires, the Appropriate Commission may, on`
  line `application, or with the consent of the licensee, revoke his licence as to the whole or any part of his area`
  line `of distribution or transmission or trading upon such terms and conditions as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) No licence shall be revoked under sub-section (1) unless the Appropriate Commission has given`
  line `to the licensee not less than three months' notice, in writing, stating the grounds on which it is proposed to revoke the licence, and has considered any cause shown by the licensee within the period of that notice,`
  line `against the proposed revocation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appropriate Commission may, instead of revoking a licence under sub-section (1), permit it`
  line `to remain in force subject to such further terms and conditions as it thinks fit to impose, and any further`
  line `terms and conditions so imposed shall be binding upon and be observed by the licensee and shall be of`
  line `like force and effect as if they were contained in the licence.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Commission revokes a licence under this section, it shall serve a notice of revocation`
  line `upon the licensee and fix a date on which the revocation shall take effect.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Appropriate Commission has given notice for revocation of licence under`
  line `sub-section (5), without prejudice to any penalty which may be imposed or prosecution proceeding which`
  line `may be initiated under this Act, the licensee may, after prior approval of that Commission, sell his utility`
  line `to any person who is found eligible by that Commission for grant of licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (11172)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Sale of utilities of licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11172&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Appropriate Commission revokes under section 19`
  line `the licence of any licensee, the following provisions shall apply, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Appropriate Commission shall invite applications for acquiring the utility of the licensee`
  line `whose licence has been revoked and determine which of such applications should be accepted,`
  line `primarily on the basis of the highest and best price offered for the utility;`
  line
  line `(b) the Appropriate Commission may, by notice in writing, require the licensee to sell his utility`
  line `and thereupon the licensee shall sell his utility to the person (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `"purchaser") whose application has been accepted by that Commission;`
  line
  line `(c) all the rights, duties, obligations and liabilities of the licensee, on and from the date of`
  line `revocation of licence or on and from the date, if earlier, on which the utility of the licensee is sold to a`
  line `purchaser, shall absolutely cease except for any liabilities which have accrued prior to that date;`
  line
  line `(d) the Appropriate Commission may make such interim arrangements in regard to the operation`
  line `of the utility as may be considered appropriate including the appointment of Administrators;`
  line
  line `(e) The Administrator appointed under clause (d) shall exercise such powers and discharge such`
  line `functions as the Appropriate Commission may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a utility is sold under sub-section (1), the purchaser shall pay to the licensee the purchase`
  line `price of the utility in such manner as may be agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Appropriate Commission issues any notice under sub-section (1) requiring the licensee`
  line `to sell the utility, it may, by such notice, require the licensee to deliver the utility, and thereupon the`
  line `licensee shall deliver on a date specified in the notice, the utility to the designated purchaser on payment`
  line `of the purchase price thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the licensee has delivered the utility referred to in sub-section (3) to the purchaser but its`
  line `sale has not been completed by the date fixed in the notice issued under that sub-section, the Appropriate`
  line `Commission may, if it deems fit, permit the intending purchaser to operate and maintain the utility system`
  line `pending the completion of the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (11173)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Vesting of utility in purchaser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11173&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where a utility is sold under section 20 or section 24, then, upon`
  line `completion of the sale or on the date on which the utility is delivered to the intending purchaser, as the`
  line `case may be, whichever is earlier--`
  line
  line `(a) the utility shall vest in the purchaser or the intending purchaser, as the case may be, free from`
  line `any debt, mortgage or similar obligation of the licensee or attaching to the utility:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such debt, mortgage or similar obligation shall attach to the purchase money in`
  line `substitution for the utility; and`
  line
  line `(b) the rights, powers, authorities, duties and obligations of the licensee under his licence shall`
  line `stand transferred to the purchaser and such purchaser shall be deemed to be the licensee.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (11174)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Provisions where no purchase takes place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11174&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the utility is not sold in the manner provided`
  line `under section 20 or section 24, the Appropriate Commission may, to protect the interest of consumers or`
  line `in the public interest, issue such directions or formulate such scheme as it may deem necessary for`
  line `operation of the utility.`
  line
  line `(2) Where no directions are issued or scheme is formulated by the Appropriate Commission under`
  line `sub-section (1), the licensee referred to in section 20 or section 24 may dispose of the utility in such`
  line `manner as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the licensee does not dispose of the utility, within a period of six months from the`
  line `date of revocation, under section 20 or section 24, the Appropriate Commission may cause the works of`
  line `the licensee in, under, over, along, or across any street or public land to be removed and every such street`
  line `or public land to be reinstated, and recover the cost of such removal and reinstatement from the licensee.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (11175)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Directions to licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11175&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If the Appropriate Commission is of the opinion that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do for maintaining the efficient supply, securing the equitable distribution of electricity`
  line `and promoting competition, it may, by order, provide for regulating supply, distribution, consumption or`
  line `use thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (11176)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Suspension of distribution licence and sale of utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11176&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Appropriate`
  line `Commission is of the opinion that a distribution licensee--`
  line
  line `(a) has persistently failed to maintain uninterrupted supply of electricity conforming to standards`
  line `regarding quality of electricity to the consumers; or`
  line
  line `(b) is unable to discharge the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the`
  line `provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given by the Appropriate`
  line `Commission under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) has broken the terms and conditions of licence,`
  line
  line `and circumstances exist which render it necessary for it in public interest so to do, the Appropriate`
  line `Commission may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, suspend, for a period not exceeding one year,`
  line `the licence of the distribution licensee and appoint an Administrator to discharge the functions of the`
  line `distribution licensee in accordance with the terms and conditions of the licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that before suspending a licence under this section, the Appropriate Commission shall`
  line `give a reasonable opportunity to the distribution licensee to make representations against the proposed`
  line `suspension of license and shall consider the representations, if any, of the distribution licensee.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon suspension of licence under sub-section (1) the utilities of the distribution licensee shall`
  line `vest in the Administrator for a period not exceeding one year or up to the date on which such utility is`
  line `sold in accordance with the provisions contained in section 20, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appropriate Commission shall, within one year of appointment of the Administrator`
  line `under sub-section (1) either revoke the licence in accordance with the provisions contained in section`
  line `19 or revoke suspension of the licence and restore the utility to the distribution licensee whose licence`
  line `had been suspended, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) In a case where the Appropriate Commission revokes the licence under sub-section (3), the`
  line `utility of the distribution licensee shall be sold within a period of one year from the date of revocation`
  line `of the licence in accordance with the provisions of section 20 and the price after deducting the`
  line `administrative and other expenses on sale of utilities be remitted to the distribution licensee.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (11177)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Inter-State, regional and inter-regional transmission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11177&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Part, the Central`
  line `Government may, make region-wise demarcation of the country, and, from time to time, make such`
  line `modifications therein as it may consider necessary for the efficient, economical and integrated`
  line `transmission and supply of electricity, and in particular to facilitate voluntary inter-connections and coordination`
  line `of facilities for the inter-State, regional and inter-regional generation and transmission of`
  line electricity.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (11178)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `National Load Despatch Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11178&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may establish a centre at the`
  line `national level, to be known as the National Load Despatch Centre for optimum scheduling and despatch`
  line `of electricity among the Regional Load Despatch Centres.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution and functions of the National Load Despatch Centre shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Load Despatch Centre shall not engage in the business of trading in`
  line electricity.
  line
  line `(3) The National Load Despatch Centre shall be operated by a Government company or any authority`
  line `or corporation established or constituted by or under any Central Act, as may be notified by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (11179)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Constitution of Regional Load Despatch Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11179&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall establish a`
  line `centre for each region to be known as the Regional Load Despatch Centre having territorial jurisdiction as`
  line `determined by the Central Government in accordance with section 25 for the purposes of exercising the`
  line `powers and discharging the functions under this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Load Despatch Centre shall be operated by a Government company or any authority`
  line `or corporation established or constituted by or under any Central Act, as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that until a Government company or authority or corporation referred to in this sub-section`
  line `is notified by the Central Government, the Central Transmission Utility shall operate the Regional Load`
  line `Despatch Centre:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Regional Load Despatch Centre shall engage in the business of generation of`
  line `electricity or trading in electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (11180)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Functions of Regional Load Despatch Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11180&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Regional Load Despatch Centre shall be`
  line `the apex body to ensure integrated operation of the power system in the concerned region.`
  line
  line `(2) The Regional Load Despatch Centre shall comply with such principles, guidelines and`
  line `methodologies in respect of the wheeling and optimum scheduling and despatch of electricity as the`
  line `Central Commission may specify in the Grid Code.`
  line
  line `(3) The Regional Load Despatch Centre shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be responsible for optimum scheduling and despatch of electricity within the region, in`
  line `accordance with the contracts entered into with the licensees or the generating companies operating in`
  line `the region;`
  line
  line `(b) monitor grid operations;`
  line
  line `(c) keep accounts of quantity of electricity transmitted through the regional grid;`
  line
  line `(d) exercise supervision and control over the inter-State transmission system; and`
  line
  line `(e) be responsible for carrying out real time operations for grid control and despatch of electricity`
  line `within the region through secure and economic operation of the regional grid in accordance with the`
  line `Grid Standards and the Grid Code.`
  line
  line `(4) The Regional Load Despatch Centre may levy and collect such fee and charges from the`
  line `generating companies or licensees engaged in inter-State transmission of electricity as may be specified`
  line `by the Central Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (11181)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Compliance of directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11181&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Regional Load Despatch Centre may give such directions and`
  line `exercise such supervision and control as may be required for ensuring stability of grid operations and for`
  line `achieving the maximum economy and efficiency in the operation of the power system in the region under`
  line `its control.`
  line
  line `(2) Every licensee, generating company, generating station, sub-station and any other person`
  line `connected with the operation of the power system shall comply with the directions issued by the Regional`
  line `Load Despatch Centres under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) All directions issued by the Regional Load Despatch Centres to any transmission licensee of State`
  line `transmission lines or any other licensee of the State or generating company (other than those connected to`
  line `inter-State transmission system) or sub-station in the State shall be issued through the State Load`
  line `Despatch Centre and the State Load Despatch Centres shall ensure that such directions are duly complied`
  line `with the licensee or generating company or sub-station.`
  line
  line `(4) The Regional Power Committee in the region may, from time to time, agree on matters`
  line `concerning the stability and smooth operation of the integrated grid and economy and efficiency in the`
  line `operation of the power system in that region.`
  line
  line `(5) If any dispute arises with reference to the quality of electricity or safe, secure and integrated`
  line `operation of the regional grid or in relation to any direction given under sub-section (1), it shall be`
  line `referred to the Central Commission for decision:`
  line
  line `Provided that pending the decision of the Central Commission, the directions of the Regional Load`
  line `Despatch Centre shall be complied with by the State Load Despatch Centre or the licensee or the`
  line `generating company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) If any licensee, generating company or any other person fails to comply with the directions issued`
  line `under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding rupees fifteen lacs.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (11182)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Transmission within a State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11182&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The State Commission shall facilitate and promote transmission,`
  line `wheeling and inter-connection arrangements within its territorial jurisdiction for the transmission and`
  line `supply of electricity by economical and efficient utilisation of the electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (11183)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Constitution of State Load Despatch Centres.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11183&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall establish a`
  line `Centre to be known as the State Load Despatch Centre for the purposes of exercising the powers and`
  line `discharging the functions under this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Load Despatch Centre shall be operated by a Government company or any authority or`
  line `corporation established or constituted by or under any State Act, as may be notified by the State`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that until a Government company or any authority or corporation is notified by the State`
  line `Government, the State Transmission Utility shall operate the State Load Despatch Centre:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no State Load Despatch Centre shall engage in the business of trading in`
  line electricity.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (11184)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Functions of State Load Despatch Centres.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11184&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Load Despatch Centre shall be the`
  line `apex body to ensure integrated operation of the power system in a State.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Load Despatch Centre shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be responsible for optimum scheduling and despatch of electricity within a State, in`
  line `accordance with the contracts entered into with the licensees or the generating companies operating in`
  line `that State;`
  line
  line `(b) monitor grid operations;`
  line
  line `(c) keep accounts of the quantity of electricity transmitted through the State grid;`
  line
  line `(d) exercise supervision and control over the intra-State transmission system; and`
  line
  line `(e) be responsible for carrying out real time operations for grid control and despatch of electricity`
  line `within the State through secure and economic operation of the State grid in accordance with the Grid`
  line `Standards and the State Grid Code.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Load Despatch Centre may levy and collect such fee and charges from the generating`
  line `companies and licensees engaged in intra-State transmission of electricity as may be specified by the`
  line `State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (11185)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Compliance of directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11185&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Load Despatch Centre in a State may give such`
  line `directions and exercise such supervision and control as may be required for ensuring the integrated grid`
  line `operations and for achieving the maximum economy and efficiency in the operation of power system in`
  line `that State.`
  line
  line `(2) Every licensee, generating company, generating station, sub-station and any other person`
  line `connected with the operation of the power system shall comply with the directions issued by the State`
  line `Load Depatch Centre under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The State Load Despatch Centre shall comply with the directions of the Regional Load Despatch`
  line Centre.
  line
  line `(4) If any dispute arises with reference to the quality of electricity or safe, secure and integrated`
  line `operation of the State grid or in relation to any direction given under sub-section (1), it shall be referred to`
  line `the State Commission for decision:`
  line
  line `Provided that pending the decision of the State Commission, the directions of the State Load`
  line `Despatch Centre shall be complied with by the licensee or generating company.`
  line
  line `(5) If any licensee, generating company or any other person fails to comply with the directions issued`
  line `under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding rupees five lacs.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (11186)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Grid Standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11186&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every transmission licensee shall comply with such technical standards, of`
  line `operation and maintenance of transmission lines, in accordance with the Grid Standards, as may be`
  line `specified by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (11187)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Intervening transmission facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11187&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may, on an application by`
  line `any licensee, by order require any other licensee owning or operating intervening transmission facilities to`
  line `provide the use of such facilities to the extent of surplus capacity available with such licensee:`
  line
  line `Provided that any dispute, regarding the extent of surplus capacity available with the licensee, shall be`
  line `adjudicated upon by the Appropriate Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (11188)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Charges for intervening transmission facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11188&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every licensee shall, on an order made`
  line `under section 35, provide his intervening transmission facilities at rates, charges and terms and conditions`
  line `as may be mutually agreed upon:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appropriate Commission may specify rates, charges and terms and conditions if`
  line `these cannot be mutually agreed upon by the licensees.`
  line
  line `(2) The rates, charges and terms and conditions referred to in sub-section (1) shall be fair and`
  line `reasonable, and may be allocated in proportion to the use of such facilities.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sections 35 and 36, the expression "intervening transmission`
  line `facilities" means the electric lines owned or operated by a licensee where such electric lines can be`
  line `utilised for transmitting electricity for and on behalf of another licensee at his request and on payment of a`
  line `tariff or charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (11189)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Directions by Appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11189&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Government may issue directions to`
  line `the Regional Load Despatch Centres or State Load Despatch Centres, as the case may be, to take such`
  line `measures as may be necessary for maintaining smooth and stable transmission and supply of electricity to`
  line `any region or State.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (11190)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Central Transmission Utility and functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11190&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may notify any`
  line `Government company as the Central Transmission Utility:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Transmission Utility shall not engage in the business of generation of`
  line `electricity or trading in electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may transfer, and vest any property, interest in`
  line `property, rights and liabilities connected with, and personnel involved in transmission of electricity of`
  line `such Central Transmission Utility, to a company or companies to be incorporated under the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) to function as a transmission licensee, through a transfer scheme to be effected in`
  line `the manner specified under Part XIII and such company or companies shall be deemed to be transmission`
  line `licensees under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions of the Central Transmission Utility shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to undertake transmission of electricity through inter-State transmission system;`
  line
  line `(b) to discharge all functions of planning and co-ordination relating to inter-State transmission`
  line `system with--`
  line
  line `(i) State Transmission Utilities;`
  line
  line `(ii) Central Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) State Governments;`
  line
  line `(iv) generating companies;`
  line
  line `(v) Regional Power Committees;`
  line
  line `(vi) Authority;`
  line
  line `(vii) licensees;`
  line
  line `(viii) any other person notified by the Central Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) to ensure development of an efficient, co-ordinated and economical system of inter-State`
  line `transmission lines for smooth flow of electricity from generating stations to the load centres;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide non-discriminatory open access to its transmission system for use by--`
  line
  line `(i) any licensee or generating company on payment of the transmission charges; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any consumer as and when such open access is provided by the State Commission under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 42, on payment of the transmission charges and a surcharge thereon, as`
  line `may be specified by the Central Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that such surcharge shall be utilised for the purpose of meeting the requirement of`
  line `current level cross-subsidy:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such surcharge and cross subsidies shall be progressively reduced ^1`
  line `*** in`
  line `the manner as may be specified by the Central Commission:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `Provided also that the manner of payment and utilisation of the surcharge shall be specified by the`
  line `Central Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such surcharge shall not be leviable in case open access is provided to a person`
  line `who has established a captive generating plant for carrying the electricity to the destination of his own`
  line use.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and eliminated" omitted by Act 26 of 2007, s. 4 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The third proviso omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007)`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (11191)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `State Transmission Utility and functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11191&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may notify the Board or a`
  line `Government company as the State Transmission Utility:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Transmission Utility shall not engage in the business of trading in electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may transfer, and vest any property, interest in property,`
  line `rights and liabilities connected with, and personnel involved in transmission of electricity, of such State`
  line `Transmission Utility, to a company or companies to be incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956) to function as transmission licensee through a transfer scheme to be effected in the manner`
  line `specified under Part XIII and such company or companies shall be deemed to be transmission licensees`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions of the State Transmission Utility shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to undertake transmission of electricity through intra-State transmission system;`
  line
  line `(b) to discharge all functions of planning and co-ordination relating to intra-State transmission`
  line `system with--`
  line
  line `(i) Central Transmission Utility;`
  line
  line `(ii) State Governments;`
  line
  line `(iii) generating companies;`
  line
  line `(iv) Regional Power Committees;`
  line
  line `(v) Authority;`
  line
  line `(vi) licensees;`
  line
  line `(vii) any other person notified by the State Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) to ensure development of an efficient, co-ordinated and economical system of intra-State`
  line `transmission lines for smooth flow of electricity from a generating station to the load centres;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide non-discriminatory open access to its transmission system for use by--`
  line
  line `(i) any licensee or generating company on payment of the transmission charges; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any consumer as and when such open access is provided by the State Commission under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 42, on payment of the transmission charges and a surcharge thereon, as`
  line `may be specified by the State Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that such surcharge shall be utilised for the purpose of meeting the requirement of`
  line `current level cross-subsidy:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such surcharge and cross subsidies shall be progressively reduced ^1`
  line ***
  line `in the manner as may be specified by the State Commission:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `Provided also that the manner of payment and utilisation of the surcharge shall be specified by the`
  line `State Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such surcharge shall not be leviable in case open access is provided to a person`
  line `who has established a captive generating plant for carrying the electricity to the destination of his own`
  line use.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and eliminated" omitted by Act 26 of 2007, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The third proviso omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (11192)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Duties of transmission licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11192&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of a transmission licensee--`
  line
  line `(a) to build, maintain and operate an efficient, co-ordinated and economical inter-State`
  line `transmission system or intra-State transmission system, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) to comply with the directions of the Regional Load Despatch Centre and the State Load`
  line `Despatch Centre, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide non-discriminatory open access to its transmission system for use by--`
  line
  line `(i) any licensee or generating company on payment of the transmission charges; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any consumer as and when such open access is provided by the State Commission under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 42, on payment of the transmission charges and a surcharge thereon, as`
  line `may be specified by the State Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that such surcharge shall be utilised for the purpose of meeting the requirement of current`
  line `level cross-subsidy:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such surcharge and cross subsidies shall be progressively reduced ^1`
  line `*** in the`
  line `manner as may be specified by the Appropriate Commission:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `Provided also that the manner of payment and utilisation of the surcharge shall be specified by the`
  line `Appropriate Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such surcharge shall not be leviable in case open access is provided to a person`
  line `who has established a captive generating plant for carrying the electricity to the destination of his own`
  line use.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and eliminated omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The third proviso omitted by Act 26 of 2007, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007)`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (11193)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Other business of transmission licensee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11193&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `A transmission licensee may, with prior intimation to`
  line `the Appropriate Commission, engage in any business for optimum utilisation of its assets:`
  line
  line `Provided that a proportion of the revenues derived from such business shall, as may be specified by`
  line `the Appropriate Commission, be utilised for reducing its charges for transmission and wheeling:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the transmission licensee shall maintain separate accounts for each such`
  line `business undertaking to ensure that transmission business neither subsidises in any way such business`
  line `undertaking nor encumbers its transmission assets in any way to support such business:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no transmission licensee shall enter into any contract or otherwise engage in the`
  line `business of trading in electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (11194)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Duties of distribution licensee and open access.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11194&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of a distribution licensee`
  line `to develop and maintain an efficient, co-ordinated and economical distribution system in his area of`
  line `supply and to supply electricity in accordance with the provisions contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall introduce open access in such phases and subject to such conditions,`
  line `(including the cross subsidies, and other operational constraints) as may be specified within one year of`
  line `the appointed date by it and in specifying the extent of open access in successive phases and in`
  line `determining the charges for wheeling, it shall have due regard to all relevant factors including such cross`
  line `subsidies, and other operational constraints:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^1`
  line `[such open access shall be allowed on payment of a surcharge in addition to the`
  line `charges] for wheeling as may be determined by the State Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such surcharge shall be utilised to meet the requirements of current level of`
  line `cross subsidy within the area of supply of the distribution licensee:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such surcharge and cross subsidies shall be progressively reduced ^2`
  line `*** in the`
  line `manner as may be specified by the State Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such surcharge shall not be leviable in case open access is provided to a person`
  line `who has established a captive generating plant for carrying the electricity to the destination of his own`
  line `use:`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[Provided also that the State Commission shall, not later than five years from the date of`
  line `commencement of the Electricity (Amendment) Act, 2003, by regulations, provide such open access to all`
  line `consumers who require a supply of electricity where the maximum power to be made available at any`
  line `time exceeds one megawatt.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person, whose premises are situated within the area of supply of a distribution`
  line `licensee, (not being a local authority engaged in the business of distribution of electricity before the`
  line `appointed date) requires a supply of electricity from a generating company or any licensee other than such`
  line `distribution licensee, such person may, by notice, require the distribution licensee for wheeling such`
  line `electricity in accordance with regulations made by the State Commission and the duties of the distribution`
  line `licensee with respect to such supply shall be of a common carrier providing non-discriminatory open`
  line access.
  line
  line `(4) Where the State Commission permits a consumer or class of consumers to receive supply of`
  line `electricity from a person other than the distribution licensee of his area of supply, such consumer shall be`
  line `liable to pay an additional surcharge on the charges of wheeling, as may be specified by the State`
  line `Commission, to meet the fixed cost of such distribution licensee arising out of his obligation to supply.`
  line
  line `(5) Every distribution licensee shall, within six months from the appointed date or date of grant of`
  line `licence, whichever is earlier, establish a forum for redressal of grievances of the consumers in accordance`
  line `with the guidelines as may be specified by the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(6) Any consumer, who is aggrieved by non-redressal of his grievances under sub-section (5), may`
  line `make a representation for the redressal of his grievance to an authority to be known as Ombudsman to be`
  line `appointed or designated by the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(7) The Ombudsman shall settle the grievance of the consumer within such time and in such manner`
  line `as may be specified by the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of sub-sections (5), (6) and (7) shall be without prejudice to right which the`
  line `consumer may have apart from the rights conferred upon him by those sub-sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s.7, ibid., for "such open access may be allowed before the cross subsidies are eliminated on payment of a surcharge"`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and eliminated" omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-1-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (11195)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Duty to supply on request.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11195&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1`
  line `[Save as otherwise provided in this Act, every distribution]`
  line `licensee, shall, on an application by the owner or occupier of any premises, give supply of electricity to`
  line `such premises, within one month after receipt of the application requiring such supply:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such supply requires extension of distribution mains, or commissioning of new`
  line `sub-stations, the distribution licensee shall supply the electricity to such premises immediately after such`
  line `extension or commissioning or within such period as may be specified by the Appropriate Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of a village or hamlet or area wherein no provision for supply of`
  line `electricity exists, the Appropriate Commission may extend the said period as it may consider necessary`
  line `for electrification of such village or hamlet or area.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "application" means the application complete in`
  line `all respects in the appropriate form, as required by the distribution licensee, along with documents`
  line `showing payment of necessary charges and other compliances.]`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every distribution licensee to provide, if required, electric plant or electric`
  line `line for giving electric supply to the premises specified in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be entitled to demand, or to continue to receive, from a licensee a`
  line `supply of electricity for any premises having a separate supply unless he has agreed with the licensee to`
  line `pay to him such price as determined by the Appropriate Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) If a distribution licensee fails to supply the electricity within the period specified in`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to one thousand rupees for each day of`
  line default.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 8, for 'Every distribution" (w.e.f. 15-6- 2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (11196)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Exceptions from duty to supply electricity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11196&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in section 43 shall be taken as`
  line `requiring a distribution licensee to give supply of electricity to any premises if he is prevented from so`
  line `doing by cyclone, floods, storms or other occurrences beyond his control.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (11197)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to recover charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11197&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, the prices to be charged`
  line `by a distribution licensee for the supply of electricity by him in pursuance of section 43 shall be in`
  line `accordance with such tariffs fixed from time to time and conditions of his licence.`
  line
  line `(2) The charges for electricity supplied by a distribution licensee shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) fixed in accordance with the methods and the principles as may be specified by the concerned`
  line `State Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) published in such manner so as to give adequate publicity for such charges and prices.`
  line
  line `(3) The charges for electricity supplied by a distribution licensee may include--`
  line
  line `(a) a fixed charge in addition to the charge for the actual electricity supplied;`
  line
  line `(b) a rent or other charges in respect of any electric meter or electrical plant provided by the`
  line `distribution licensee.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of section 62, in fixing charges under this section a distribution licensee`
  line `shall not show undue preference to any person or class of persons or discrimination against any person or`
  line `class of persons.`
  line
  line `(5) The charges fixed by the distribution licensee shall be in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Act and the regulations made in this behalf by the concerned State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (11198)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to recover expenditure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11198&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The State Commission may, by regulations, authorise a`
  line `distribution licensee to charge from a person requiring a supply of electricity in pursuance of section 43`
  line `any expenses reasonably incurred in providing any electric line or electrical plant used for the purpose of`
  line `giving that supply.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (11199)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to require security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11199&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, a distribution licensee`
  line `may require any person, who requires a supply of electricity in pursuance of section 43, to give him`
  line `reasonable security, as may be determined by regulations, for the payment to him of all monies which`
  line `may become due to him--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the electricity supplied to such persons; or`
  line
  line `(b) where any electric line or electrical plant or electric meter is to be provided for supplying`
  line `electricity to such person, in respect of the provision of such line or plant or meter,`
  line
  line `and if that person fails to give such security, the distribution licensee may, if he thinks fit, refuse to give`
  line `the supply of electricity or to provide the line or plant or meter for the period during which the failure`
  line continues.
  line
  line `(2) Where any person has not given such security as is mentioned in sub-section (1) or the security`
  line `given by any person has become invalid or insufficient, the distribution licensee may, by notice, require`
  line `that person, within thirty days after the service of the notice, to give him reasonable security for the payment of all monies which may become due to him in respect of the supply of electricity or provision`
  line `of such line or plant or meter.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person referred to in sub-section (2) fails to give such security, the distribution licensee may,`
  line `if he thinks fit, discontinue the supply of electricity for the period during which the failure continues.`
  line
  line `(4) The distribution licensee shall pay interest equivalent to the bank rate or more, as may be`
  line `specified by the concerned State Commission, on the security referred to in sub-section (1) and refund`
  line `such security on the request of the person who gave such security.`
  line
  line `(5) A distribution licensee shall not be entitled to require security in pursuance of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) if the person requiring the supply is prepared to take the supply through a pre-payment`
  line meter.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (11200)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Additional terms of supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11200&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `A distribution licensee may require any person who requires a`
  line `supply of electricity in pursuance of section 43 to accept--`
  line
  line `(a) any restrictions which may be imposed for the purpose of enabling the distribution licensee to`
  line `comply with the regulations made under section 53;`
  line
  line `(b) any terms restricting any liability of the distribution licensee for economic loss resulting from`
  line `negligence of the person to whom the electricity is supplied.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (11201)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Agreements with respect to supply or purchase of electricity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11201&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where the Appropriate`
  line `Commission has allowed open access to certain consumers under section 42, such consumers,`
  line `notwithstanding the provisions contained in clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 62, may enter into an`
  line `agreement with any person for supply or purchase of electricity on such terms and conditions (including`
  line `tariff) as may be agreed upon by them.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (11202)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `The Electricity supply code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 9, for section 50 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11202&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[50. The Electricity supply code.–The State Commission shall specify an electricity supply code to`
  line `provide for recovery of electricity charges, intervals for billing of electricity charges, disconnection of`
  line `supply of electricity for non-payment thereof, restoration of supply of electricity, measures for preventing`
  line `tampering, distress or damage to electrical plant or electrical line or meter, entry of distribution licensee`
  line `or any person acting on his behalf for disconnecting supply and removing the meter, entry for replacing,`
  line `altering or maintaining electric lines or electrical plants or meter and such other matters.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (11203)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Other businesses of distribution licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11203&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `A distribution licensee may, with prior intimation to`
  line `the Appropriate Commission, engage in any other business for optimum utilisation of its assets:`
  line
  line `Provided that a proportion of the revenues derived from such business shall, as may be specified by`
  line `the concerned State Commission, be utilised for reducing its charges for wheeling:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the distribution licensee shall maintain separate accounts for each such business`
  line `undertaking to ensure that distribution business neither subsidises in any way such business undertaking`
  line `nor encumbers its distribution assets in any way to support such business:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing contained in this section shall apply to a local authority engaged, before`
  line `the commencement of this Act, in the business of distribution of electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (11204)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Provisions with respect to electricity trader.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11204&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained`
  line `in clause (c) of section 12, the Appropriate Commission may, specify the technical requirement, capital`
  line `adequacy requirement and creditworthiness for being an electricity trader.`
  line
  line `(2) Every electricity trader shall discharge such duties, in relation to supply and trading in electricity,`
  line `as may be specified by the Appropriate Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (11205)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Provision relating to safety and electricity supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11205&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, in consultation with the`
  line `State Government, specify suitable measures for--`
  line
  line `(a) protecting the public (including the persons engaged in the generation, transmission or`
  line `distribution or trading) from dangers arising from the generation, transmission or distribution or`
  line `trading of electricity, or use of electricity supplied or installation, maintenance or use of any electric`
  line `line or electrical plant;`
  line
  line `(b) eliminating or reducing the risks of personal injury to any person, or damage to property of`
  line `any person or interference with use of such property;`
  line
  line `(c) prohibiting the supply or transmission of electricity except by means of a system which`
  line `conforms to the specifications as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(d) giving notice in the specified form to the Appropriate Commission and the Electrical`
  line `Inspector, of accidents and failures of supplies or transmissions of electricity;`
  line
  line `(e) keeping by a generating company or licensee the maps, plans and sections relating to supply`
  line `or transmission of electricity;`
  line
  line `(f) inspection of maps, plans and sections by any person authorised by it or by Electrical Inspector`
  line `or by any person on payment of specified fee;`
  line
  line `(g) specifying action to be taken in relation to any electric line or electrical plant, or any electrical`
  line `appliance under the control of a consumer for the purpose of eliminating or reducing the risk of`
  line `personal injury or damage to property or interference with its use.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of sections 53A.--In the Electricity Act, 2003 (Central Act 36 of 2003) (herein after referred`
  line `to as Principal Act), after section 53, the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `53-A. Powers of State Government relating to Safety and Electricity supply.--Where Central`
  line `Government or the Authority has made no provision relating to following Safety measures and`
  line `electricity supply the State Government may by rules provide for,--`
  line
  line `(a) terms and Conditions and manner of Inspection by the Chief Electrical Inspector and`
  line `Electrical Inspectors;`
  line
  line `(b) manner of Issue of Licence to electrical contractors, Permits to Supervisors and wiremen`
  line `and competency certificates;`
  line
  line `(c) manner of Scrutiny and approval of Electrical Installation drawings,`
  line
  line `(d) levy of fee for the Inspection or other services rendered by the Chief Electrical Inspector`
  line `or the Electrical Inspectors; and`
  line
  line `(e) the rate and manner of collection of fee. If not remitted within the stipulated time, to`
  line `recover the same as an arrears of Land revenue.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 39 of 2014, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (11206)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Control of transmission and use of electricity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11206&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise exempted under this Act,`
  line `no person other than the Central Transmission Utility or a State Transmission Utility, or a licensee shall`
  line `transmit or use electricity at a rate exceeding two hundred and fifty watts and one hundred volts--`
  line
  line `(a) in any street, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any place,--`
  line
  line `(i) in which one hundred or more persons are ordinarily likely to be assembled; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is a factory within the meaning of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948) or a mine`
  line `within the meaning of the Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 1952); or`
  line
  line `(iii) to which the State Government, by general or special order, declares the provisions of`
  line `this sub-section to apply,`
  line
  line `without giving, before the commencement of transmission or use of electricity, not less than seven days'`
  line `notice in writing of his intention to the Electrical Inspector and to the District Magistrate or the`
  line `Commissioner of Police, as the case may be, containing particulars of the electrical installation and plant,`
  line `if any, the nature and the purpose of supply and complying with such of the provisions of Part XVII of`
  line `this Act, as may be applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to electricity used for the public carriage of`
  line `passengers, animals or goods, on, or for the lighting or ventilation of the rolling stock of any railway or`
  line `tramway subject to the provisions of the Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989).`
  line
  line `(2) Where any difference or dispute arises as to whether a place is or is not one in which one hundred`
  line `or more persons are ordinarily likely to be assembled, the matter shall be referred to the State`
  line `Government, and the decision of the State Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall be binding on the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (11207)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Use, etc., of meters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11207&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) No licensee shall supply electricity, after the expiry of two years from`
  line `the appointed date, except through installation of a correct meter in accordance with the regulations to be`
  line `made in this behalf by the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the licensee may require the consumer to give him security for the price of a meter and`
  line `enter into an agreement for the hire thereof, unless the consumer elects to purchase a meter:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Commission may, by notification, extend the said period of two years`
  line `for a class or classes of persons or for such area as may be specified in that notification.`
  line
  line `(2) For proper accounting and audit in the generation, transmission and distribution or trading of`
  line `electricity, the Authority may direct the installation of meters by a generating company or licensee at such`
  line `stages of generation, transmission or distribution or trading of electricity and at such locations of`
  line `generation, transmission or distribution or trading , as it may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) If a person makes default in complying with the provisions contained in this section or the`
  line `regulations made under sub-section (1), the Appropriate Commission may make such order as it thinks fit`
  line `for requiring the default to be made good by the generating company or licensee or by any officers of a`
  line `company or other association or any other person who is responsible for its default.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (11208)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Disconnection of supply in default of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11208&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person neglects to pay any`
  line `charge for electricity or any sum other than a charge for electricity due from him to a licensee or the`
  line `generating company in respect of supply, transmission or distribution or wheeling of electricity to him,`
  line `the licensee or the generating company may, after giving not less than fifteen clear days' notice in`
  line `writing, to such person and without prejudice to his rights to recover such charge or other sum by suit, cut`
  line `off the supply of electricity and for that purpose cut or disconnect any electric supply line or other works`
  line `being the property of such licensee or the generating company through which electricity may have been`
  line `supplied, transmitted, distributed or wheeled and may discontinue the supply until such charge or other`
  line `sum, together with any expenses incurred by him in cutting off and reconnecting the supply, are paid, but`
  line `no longer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the supply of electricity shall not be cut off if such person deposits, under protest,--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the sum claimed from him, or`
  line
  line `(b) the electricity charges due from him for each month calculated on the basis of average charge`
  line `for electricity paid by him during the preceding six months,`
  line
  line `whichever is less, pending disposal of any dispute between him and the licensee.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no sum due from`
  line `any consumer, under this section shall be recoverable after the period of two years from the date when`
  line `such sum became first due unless such sum has been shown continuously as recoverable as arrear of`
  line `charges for electricity supplied and the licensee shall not cut off the supply of the electricity.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (11209)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Standards of performance of licensee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11209&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Commission may, after consultation`
  line `with the licensees and persons likely to be affected, specify standards of performance of a licensee or a`
  line `class of licensees.`
  line
  line `(2) If a licensee fails to meet the standards specified under sub-section (1), without prejudice to any`
  line `penalty which may be imposed or prosecution be initiated, he shall be liable to pay such compensation to`
  line `the person affected as may be determined by the Appropriate Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that before determination of compensation, the concerned licensee shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) The compensation determined under sub-section (2) shall be paid by the concerned licensee`
  line `within ninety days of such determination.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (11210)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Different standards of performance by licensee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11210&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may specify`
  line `different standards under sub-section (1) of section 57 for a class or classes of licensees.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (11211)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Information with respect to levels of performance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11211&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every licensee shall, within the period`
  line `specified by the Appropriate Commission, furnish to the Commission the following information,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the level of performance achieved under sub-section (1) of the section 57;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of cases in which compensation was made under sub-section (2) of section 57 and`
  line `the aggregate amount of the compensation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Commission shall at least once in every year arrange for the publication, in such`
  line `form and manner as it considers appropriate, of such of the information furnished to it under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (11212)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Market domination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11212&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may issue such directions as it considers`
  line `appropriate to a licensee or a generating company if such licensee or generating company enters into any`
  line `agreement or abuses its dominant position or enters into a combination which is likely to cause or causes`
  line `an adverse effect on competition in electricity industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (11213)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Tariff regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 10, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11213&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission shall, subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `specify the terms and conditions for the determination of tariff, and in doing so, shall be guided by the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles and methodologies specified by the Central Commission for determination of`
  line `the tariff applicable to generating companies and transmission licensees;`
  line
  line `(b) the generation, transmission, distribution and supply of electricity are conducted on`
  line `commercial principles;`
  line
  line `(c) the factors which would encourage competition, efficiency, economical use of the resources,`
  line `good performance and optimum investments;`
  line
  line `(d) safeguarding of consumers' interest and at the same time, recovery of the cost of electricity in`
  line `a reasonable manner;`
  line
  line `(e) the principles rewarding efficiency in performance;`
  line
  line `(f) multi year tariff principles;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(g) that the tariff progressively reflects the cost of supply of electricity and also, reduces`
  line `cross-subsidies in the manner specified by the Appropriate Commission;]`
  line
  line `(h) the promotion of co-generation and generation of electricity from renewable sources of`
  line energy;
  line
  line `(i) the National Electricity Policy and tariff policy:`
  line
  line `Provided that the terms and conditions for determination of tariff under the Electricity (Supply) Act,`
  line `1948 (54 of 1948), the Electricity Regulatory Commission Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) and the enactments`
  line `specified in the Schedule as they stood immediately before the appointed date, shall continue to apply for`
  line `a period of one year or until the terms and conditions for tariff are specified under this section, whichever`
  line `is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (11214)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Determination of tariff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11214&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Commission shall determine the tariff in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act for--`
  line
  line `(a) supply of electricity by a generating company to a distribution licensee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appropriate Commission may, in case of shortage of supply of electricity, fix`
  line `the minimum and maximum ceiling of tariff for sale or purchase of electricity in pursuance of an`
  line `agreement, entered into between a generating company and a licensee or between licensees, for a`
  line `period not exceeding one year to ensure reasonable prices of electricity;`
  line
  line `(b) transmission of electricity;`
  line
  line `(c) wheeling of electricity;`
  line
  line `(d) retail sale of electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of distribution of electricity in the same area by two or more distribution`
  line `licensees, the Appropriate Commission may, for promoting competition among distribution licensees, fix`
  line `only maximum ceiling of tariff for retail sale of electricity.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Commission may require a licensee or a generating company to furnish separate`
  line `details, as may be specified in respect of generation, transmission and distribution for determination of`
  line tariff.
  line
  line `(3) The Appropriate Commission shall not, while determining the tariff under this Act, show undue`
  line `preference to any consumer of electricity but may differentiate according to the consumer's load factor,`
  line `power factor, voltage, total consumption of electricity during any specified period or the time at which the`
  line `supply is required or the geographical position of any area, the nature of supply and the purpose for which`
  line `the supply is required.`
  line
  line `(4) No tariff or part of any tariff may ordinarily be amended, more frequently than once in any`
  line `financial year, except in respect of any changes expressly permitted under the terms of any fuel surcharge`
  line `formula as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission may require a licensee or a generating company to comply with such procedures`
  line `as may be specified for calculating the expected revenues from the tariff and charges which he or it is`
  line `permitted to recover.`
  line
  line `(6) If any licensee or a generating company recovers a price or charge exceeding the tariff determined`
  line `under this section, the excess amount shall be recoverable by the person who has paid such price or`
  line `charge along with interest equivalent to the bank rate without prejudice to any other liability incurred by`
  line `the licensee.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (11215)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Determination of tariff by bidding process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11215&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 62,`
  line `the Appropriate Commission shall adopt the tariff if such tariff has been determined through transparent`
  line `process of bidding in accordance with the guidelines issued by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (11216)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Procedure for tariff order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11216&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for determination of tariff under section 62 shall`
  line `be made by a generating company or licensee in such manner and accompanied by such fee, as may be`
  line `determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every applicant shall publish the application, in such abridged form and manner, as may be`
  line `specified by the Appropriate Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appropriate Commission shall, within one hundred and twenty days from receipt of an`
  line `application under sub-section (1) and after considering all suggestions and objections received from the`
  line public,--
  line
  line `(a) issue a tariff order accepting the application with such modifications or such conditions as`
  line `may be specified in that order;`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application for reasons to be recorded in writing if such application is not in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder or the`
  line `provisions of any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that an applicant shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard before rejecting his`
  line application.
  line
  line `(4) The Appropriate Commission shall, within seven days of making the order, send a copy of the`
  line `order to the Appropriate Government, the Authority, and the concerned licensees and to the person`
  line concerned.
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in Part X, the tariff for any inter-State supply, transmission or`
  line `wheeling of electricity, as the case may be, involving the territories of two States may, upon application`
  line `made to it by the parties intending to undertake such supply, transmission or wheeling, be determined`
  line `under this section by the State Commission having jurisdiction in respect of the licensee who intends to`
  line `distribute electricity and make payment therefor.`
  line
  line `(6) A tariff order shall, unless amended or revoked, continue to be in force for such period as may be`
  line `specified in the tariff order.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (11217)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Provision of subsidy by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11217&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `If the State Government requires the grant of any`
  line `subsidy to any consumer or class of consumers in the tariff determined by the State Commission under`
  line `section 62, the State Government shall, notwithstanding any direction which may be given under section`
  line `108, pay, in advance and in such manner as may be specified, the amount to compensate the person`
  line `affected by the grant of subsidy in the manner the State Commission may direct, as a condition for the`
  line `licence or any other person concerned to implement the subsidy provided for by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction of the State Government shall be operative if the payment is not made`
  line `in accordance with the provisions contained in this section and the tariff fixed by the State Commission`
  line `shall be applicable from the date of issue of orders by the Commission in this regard.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (11218)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Development of market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11218&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission shall endeavour to promote the`
  line `development of a market (including trading) in power in such manner as may be specified and shall be`
  line `guided by the National Electricity Policy referred to in section 3 in this regard.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (11219)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Provision as to opening up of streets, railways, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11219&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) A licensee may, from time to time but`
  line `subject always to the terms and conditions of his licence, within his area of supply or transmission or`
  line `when permitted by the terms of his licence to lay down or place electric supply lines without the area of`
  line `supply, without that area carry out works such as--`
  line
  line `(a) to open and break up the soil and pavement of any street, railway or tramway;`
  line
  line `(b) to open and break up any sewer, drain or tunnel in or under any street, railway or tramway;`
  line
  line `(c) to alter the position of any line or works or pipes, other than a main sewer pipe;`
  line
  line `(d) to lay down and place electric lines, electrical plant and other works;`
  line
  line `(e) to repair, alter or remove the same;`
  line
  line `(f) to do all other acts necessary for transmission or supply of electricity.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Government may, by rules made by it in this behalf, specify,--`
  line
  line `(a) the cases and circumstances in which the consent in writing of the appropriate Government,`
  line `local authority, owner or occupier, as the case may be, shall be required for carrying out works;`
  line
  line `(b) the authority which may grant permission in the circumstances where the owner or occupier`
  line `objects to the carrying out of works;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature and period of notice to be given by the licensee before carrying out works;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure and manner of consideration of objections and suggestion received in`
  line `accordance with the notice referred to in clause (c);`
  line
  line `(e) the determination and payment of compensation or rent to the persons affected by works`
  line `under this section;`
  line
  line `(f) the repairs and works to be carried out when emergency exists;`
  line
  line `(g) the right of the owner or occupier to carry out certain works under this section and the`
  line `payment of expenses therefor;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for carrying out other works near sewers, pipes or other electric lines or works;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for alteration of the position of pipes, electric lines, electrical plant, telegraph`
  line `lines, sewer lines, tunnels, drains, etc.;`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure for fencing, guarding, lighting and other safety measures relating to works on`
  line `streets, railways, tramways, sewers, drains or tunnels and immediate reinstatement thereof;`
  line
  line `(k) the avoidance of public nuisance, environmental damage and unnecessary damage to the`
  line `public and private property by such works;`
  line
  line `(l) the procedure for undertaking works which are not reparable by the Appropriate Government,`
  line `licensee or local authority;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of deposit of amount required for restoration of any railways, tramways,`
  line `waterways, etc.;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of restoration of property affected by such works and maintenance thereof;`
  line
  line `(o) the procedure for deposit of compensation payable by the licensee and furnishing of security;`
  line and
  line
  line `(p) such other matters as are incidental or consequential to the construction and maintenance of`
  line `works under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) A licensee shall, in exercise of any of the powers conferred by or under this section and the rules`
  line `made thereunder, cause as little damage, detriment and inconvenience as may be, and shall make full`
  line `compensation for any damage, detriment or inconvenience caused by him or by any one employed by`
  line him.
  line
  line `(4) Where any difference or dispute [including amount of compensation under sub-section (3)] arises`
  line `under this section, the matter shall be determined by the Appropriate Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) The Appropriate Commission, while determining any difference or dispute arising under this`
  line `section in addition to any compensation under sub-section (3), may impose a penalty not exceeding the`
  line `amount of compensation payable under that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (11220)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Overhead lines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11220&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) An overhead line shall, with prior approval of the Appropriate Government,`
  line `be installed or kept installed above ground in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions contained in sub-section (1) shall not apply--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to an electric line which has a nominal voltage not exceeding 11 kilovolts and is`
  line `used or intended to be used for supplying to a single consumer;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to so much of an electric line as is or will be within premises in the occupation or`
  line `control of the person responsible for its installation; or`
  line
  line `(c) in such other cases, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appropriate Government shall, while granting approval under sub-section (1), impose such`
  line `conditions (including conditions as to the ownership and operation of the line) as appear to it to be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(4) The Appropriate Government may vary or revoke the approval at any time after the end of such`
  line `period as may be stipulated in the approval granted by it.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any tree standing or lying near an overhead line or where any structure or other object`
  line `which has been placed or has fallen near an overhead line subsequent to the placing of such line,`
  line `interrupts or interferes with, or is likely to interrupt or interfere with, the conveyance or transmission of`
  line `electricity or the accessibility of any works, an Executive Magistrate or authority specified by the`
  line `Appropriate Government may, on the application of the licensee, cause the tree, structure or object to be`
  line `removed or otherwise dealt with as he or it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(6) When disposing of an application under sub-section (5), an Executive Magistrate or authority`
  line `specified under that sub-section shall, in the case of any tree in existence before the placing of the`
  line `overhead line, award to the person interested in the tree such compensation as he thinks reasonable, and`
  line `such person may recover the same from the licensee.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "tree" shall be deemed to include any`
  line `shrub, hedge, jungle growth or other plant.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (11221)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Notice to telegraph authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11221&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) A licensee shall, before laying down or placing, within ten`
  line `meters of any telegraph line, electric line, electrical plant or other works, not being either service lines, or`
  line `electric lines or electrical plant, for the repair, renewal or amendment of existing works of which the`
  line `character or position is not to be altered,--`
  line
  line `(a) submit a proposal in case of a new installation to an authority to be designated by the Central`
  line `Government and such authority shall take a decision on the proposal within thirty days;`
  line
  line `(b) give not less than ten days' notice in writing to the telegraph authority in case of repair,`
  line `renewal or amendment of existing works, specifying--`
  line
  line `(i) the course of the works or alterations proposed;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner in which the works are to be utilised;`
  line
  line `(iii) the amount and nature of the electricity to be transmitted;`
  line
  line `(iv) the extent to, and the manner in which (if at all), earth returns are to be used,`
  line
  line `and the licensee shall conform to such reasonable requirements, either general or special, as may be laid`
  line `down by the telegraph authority within that period for preventing any telegraph line from being`
  line `injuriously affected by such works or alterations:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of emergency (which shall be stated by the licensee in writing to the telegraph`
  line `authority) arising from defects in any of the electric lines or electrical plant or other works of the licensee,`
  line `the licensee shall be required to give only such notice as may be possible after the necessity for the`
  line `proposed new works or alterations has arisen.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the works of the laying or placing of any service line is to be executed, the licensee shall,`
  line `not less than forty-eight hours before commencing the work, serve upon the telegraph authority a notice`
  line `in writing of his intention to execute such works.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (11222)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Constitution, etc., of Central Electricity Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11222&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a body to be called the`
  line `Central Electricity Authority to exercise such functions and perform such duties as are assigned to it`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Electricity Authority, established under section 3 of the Electricity (Supply) Act,`
  line `1948 (54 of 1948) and functioning as such immediately before the appointed date, shall be the Central`
  line `Electricity Authority for the purposes of this Act and the Chairperson, Members, Secretary and other`
  line `officers and employees thereof shall be deemed to have been appointed under this Act and they shall`
  line `continue to hold office on the same terms and conditions on which they were appointed under the`
  line `Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall consist of not more than fourteen Members (including its Chairperson) of`
  line `whom not more than eight shall be full-time Members to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may appoint any person, eligible to be appointed as Member of the`
  line `Authority, as the Chairperson of the Authority, or, designate one of the full-time Members as the`
  line `Chairperson of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Members of the Authority shall be appointed from amongst persons of ability, integrity and`
  line `standing who have knowledge of, and adequate experience and capacity in, dealing with problems`
  line `relating to engineering, finance, commerce, economics or industrial matters, and at least one Member`
  line `shall be appointed from each of the following categories, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) engineering with specialisation in design, construction, operation and maintenance of`
  line `generating stations;`
  line
  line `(b) engineering with specialisation in transmission and supply of electricity;`
  line
  line `(c) applied research in the field of electricity;`
  line
  line `(d) applied economics, accounting, commerce or finance.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson and all the Members of the Authority shall hold office during the pleasure of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson shall be the Chief Executive of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(8) The headquarters of the Authority shall be at Delhi.`
  line
  line `(9) The Authority shall meet at the head office or any other place at such time as the Chairperson may`
  line `direct, and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings`
  line `(including the quorum at its meetings) as it may specify.`
  line
  line `(10) The Chairperson, or if he is unable to attend a meeting of the Authority, any other Member`
  line `nominated by the Chairperson in this behalf and in the absence of such nomination or where there is no`
  line `Chairperson, any Member chosen by the Members present from among themselves shall preside at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(11) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes of the Members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson or`
  line `the person presiding shall have the right to exercise a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(12) All orders and decisions of the Authority shall be authenticated by the Secretary or any other`
  line `officer of the Authority duly authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(13) No act or proceedings of the Authority shall be questioned or shall be invalidated merely on the`
  line `ground of existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in, the constitution of, the Authority.`
  line
  line `(14) The Chairperson of the Authority and other full-time Members shall receive such salary and`
  line `allowances as may be determined by the Central Government and other Members shall receive such`
  line `allowances and fees for attending the meetings of the Authority, as the Central Government may`
  line prescribe.
  line
  line `(15) The other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and Members of the Authority`
  line `including, subject to the provisions of sub-section (6), their terms of office shall be such as the Central`
  line `Government may prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (11223)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Members not to have certain interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11223&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `No Member of the Authority shall have any share or`
  line `interest, whether in his own name or otherwise, in any company or other body corporate or an association`
  line `of persons (whether incorporated or not) or a firm engaged in the business of generation, transmission,`
  line `distribution and trading of electricity or fuel for the generation thereof or in the manufacture of electrical`
  line equipment.
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (11224)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Officers and staff of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11224&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may appoint a Secretary and such other officers`
  line `and employees as it considers necessary for the performance of its functions under this Act and on such`
  line `terms as to salary, remuneration, fee, allowance, pension, leave and gratuity, as the authority may in`
  line `consultation with the Central Government, fix:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appointment of the Secretary shall be subject to the approval of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (11225)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Functions and duties of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11225&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall perform such functions and duties as`
  line `the Central Government may prescribe or direct, and in particular to--`
  line
  line `(a) advise the Central Government on the matters relating to the national electricity policy,`
  line `formulate short-term and perspective plans for development of the electricity system and co-ordinate`
  line `the activities of the planning agencies for the optimal utilisation of resources to subserve the interests`
  line `of the national economy and to provide reliable and affordable electricity for all consumers;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the technical standards for construction of electrical plants, electric lines and`
  line `connectivity to the grid;`
  line
  line `(c) specify the safety requirements for construction, operation and maintenance of electrical`
  line `plants and electric lines;`
  line
  line `(d) specify the Grid Standards for operation and maintenance of transmission lines;`
  line
  line `(e) specify the conditions for installation of meters for transmission and supply of electricity;`
  line
  line `(f) promote and assist in the timely completion of schemes and projects for improving and`
  line `augmenting the electricity system;`
  line
  line `(g) promote measures for advancing the skill of persons engaged in the electricity industry;`
  line
  line `(h) advise the Central Government on any matter on which its advice is sought or make`
  line `recommendation to that Government on any matter if, in the opinion of the Authority, the`
  line `recommendation would help in improving the generation, transmission, trading, distribution and`
  line `utilisation of electricity;`
  line
  line `(i) collect and record the data concerning the generation, transmission, trading, distribution and`
  line `utilisation of electricity and carry out studies relating to cost, efficiency, competitiveness and such`
  line `like matters;`
  line
  line `(j) make public from time to time the information secured under this Act, and provide for the`
  line `publication of reports and investigations;`
  line
  line `(k) promote research in matters affecting the generation, transmission, distribution and trading of`
  line electricity;
  line
  line `(l) carry out, or cause to be carried out, any investigation for the purposes of generating or`
  line `transmitting or distributing electricity;`
  line
  line `(m) advise any State Government, licensees or the generating companies on such matters which`
  line `shall enable them to operate and maintain the electricity system under their ownership or control in an`
  line `improved manner and where necessary, in co-ordination with any other Government, licensee or the`
  line `generating company owning or having the control of another electricity system;`
  line
  line `(n) advise the Appropriate Government and the Appropriate Commission on all technical matters`
  line `relating to generation, transmission and distribution of electricity; and`
  line
  line `(o) discharge such other functions as may be provided under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (11226)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power to require statistics and returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11226&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every licensee, generating`
  line `company or person generating electricity for its or his own use to furnish to the Authority such statistics,`
  line `returns or other information relating to generation, transmission, distribution, trading and use of electricity`
  line `as it may require and at such times and in such form and manner as may be specified by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (11227)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Directions by Central Government to Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11227&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its functions, the`
  line `Authority shall be guided by such directions in matters of policy involving public interest as the Central`
  line `Government may give to it in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any such direction relates to a matter of policy involving`
  line `public interest, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (11228)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Constitution of Central Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11228&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Commission to be known as the`
  line `Central Electricity Regulatory Commission to exercise the powers conferred on, and discharge the`
  line `functions assigned to it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Electricity Regulatory Commission, established under section 3 of the Electricity`
  line `Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) and functioning as such immediately before the`
  line `appointed date, shall be deemed to be the Central Commission for the purposes of this Act and the`
  line `Chairperson, Members, Secretary, and other officers and employees thereof shall be deemed to have been`
  line `appointed under this Act and they shall continue to hold office on the same terms and conditions on`
  line `which they were appointed under the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson and other Members of the Central Commission appointed, before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, under the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998), may,`
  line `on the recommendations of the Selection Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of section 78, be`
  line `allowed, to opt for the terms and conditions under this Act by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Commission shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and`
  line `immovable, and to contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(4) The head office of the Central Commission shall be at such place as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Commission shall consist of the following Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson and three other Members;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairperson of the Authority who shall be the Member, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson and Members of the Central Commission shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government on the recommendation of the Selection Committee referred to in section 78.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (11229)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Members of Central Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11229&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and`
  line `the Members of the Central Commission shall be persons having adequate knowledge of, or experience`
  line `in, or shown capacity in, dealing with, problems relating to engineering, law, economics, commerce,`
  line `finance or management and shall be appointed in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) one person having qualifications and experience in the field of engineering with specialisation`
  line `in generation, transmission or distribution of electricity;`
  line
  line `(b) one person having qualifications and experience in the field of finance;`
  line
  line `(c) two persons having qualifications and experience in the field of economics, commerce, law or`
  line `management:`
  line
  line `Provided that not more than one Member shall be appointed under the same category under`
  line `clause (c).`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may appoint any`
  line `person as the Chairperson from amongst persons who is, or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court or the`
  line `Chief Justice of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appointment under this sub-section shall be made except after consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson or any other Member of the Central Commission shall not hold any other office.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall be the Chief Executive of the Central Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (11230)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Constitution of Selection Committee to recommend Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11230&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, for the purposes of selecting the Members of the Appellate Tribunal and the Chairperson and`
  line `Members of the Central Commission, constitute a Selection Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) Member of the Planning Commission incharge of the energy sector Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary-in-charge of the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with the Department`
  line `of the Legal Affairs . Member;`
  line
  line `(c) Chairperson of the Public Enterprises Selection Board .Member;`
  line
  line `(d) a person to be nominated by the Central Government in accordance with`
  line `sub-section (2) Member;`
  line
  line `(e) a person to be nominated by the Central Government in accordance with`
  line `sub-section (3).. Member;`
  line
  line `(f) Secretary-in-charge of the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with`
  line power.Member.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of clause (d) of sub-section (1), the Central Government shall nominate from`
  line `amongst persons holding the post of chairperson or managing director, by whatever name called, of any`
  line `public financial institution specified in section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of clause (e) of sub-section (1), the Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `nominate from amongst persons holding the post of director or the head of the institution, by whatever`
  line `name called, of any research, technical or management institution for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(4) Secretary-in-charge of the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Power shall be the`
  line `Convenor of the Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall, within one month from the date of occurrence of any vacancy by`
  line `reason of death, resignation or removal of a Member of the Appellate Tribunal or the Chairperson or a`
  line `Member of the Central Commission and six months before the superannuation or end of tenure of the`
  line `Member of the Appellate Tribunal or Member of the Central Commission, make a reference to the`
  line `Selection Committee for filling up of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(6) The Selection Committee shall finalise the selection of the Chairperson and Members referred to`
  line `in sub-section (5) within three months from the date on which the reference is made to it.`
  line
  line `(7) The Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of two names for every vacancy referred to it.`
  line
  line `(8) Before recommending any person for appointment as Member of the Appellate Tribunal or the`
  line `Chairperson or other Member of the Central Commission, the Selection Committee shall satisfy itself that`
  line `such person does not have any financial or other interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his`
  line `functions as the Chairperson or Member.`
  line
  line `(9) No appointment of the Chairperson or other Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any`
  line `vacancy in the Selection Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to the appointment of a person as the`
  line `Chairperson of the Central Commission where such person is, or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court`
  line `or the Chief Justice of a High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (11231)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Functions of Central Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11231&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Commission shall discharge the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to regulate the tariff of generating companies owned or controlled by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) to regulate the tariff of generating companies other than those owned or controlled by the`
  line `Central Government specified in clause (a), if such generating companies enter into or otherwise have`
  line `a composite scheme for generation and sale of electricity in more than one State;`
  line
  line `(c) to regulate the inter-State transmission of electricity;`
  line
  line `(d) to determine tariff for inter-State transmission of electricity;`
  line
  line `(e) to issue licences to persons to function as transmission licensee and electricity trader with`
  line `respect to their inter-State operations;`
  line
  line `(f) to adjudicate upon disputes involving generating companies or transmission licensee in regard`
  line `to matters connected with clauses (a) to (d) above and to refer any dispute for arbitration;`
  line
  line `(g) to levy fees for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) to specify Grid Code having regard to Grid Standards;`
  line
  line `(i) to specify and enforce the standards with respect to quality, continuity and reliability of service`
  line `by licensees;`
  line
  line `(j) to fix the trading margin in the inter-State trading of electricity, if considered, necessary;`
  line
  line `(k) to discharge such other functions as may be assigned under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Commission shall advise the Central Government on all or any of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) formulation of National electricity Policy and tariff policy;`
  line
  line `(ii) promotion of competition, efficiency and economy in activities of the electricity industry;`
  line
  line `(iii) promotion of investment in electricity industry;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other matter referred to the Central Commission by that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Commission shall ensure transparency while exercising its powers and discharging its`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(4) In discharge of its functions, the Central Commission shall be guided by the National Electricity`
  line `Policy, National Electricity Plan and tariff policy published under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (11232)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Central Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11232&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Commission may, by notification, establish with`
  line `effect from such date as it may specify in such notification, a Committee to be known as the Central`
  line `Advisory Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Advisory Committee shall consist of not more than thirty-one members to represent`
  line `the interests of commerce, industry, transport, agriculture, labour, consumers, non-governmental`
  line `organisations and academic and research bodies in the electricity sector.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the Central Commission shall be the ex officio Chairperson of the Central`
  line `Advisory Committee and the Members of that Commission and Secretary to the Government of India in`
  line `charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with Consumer Affairs and`
  line `Public Distribution System shall be the ex officio Members of the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (11233)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Objects of Central Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11233&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the Central Advisory Committee shall`
  line `be to advise the Central Commission on--`
  line
  line `(i) major questions of policy;`
  line
  line `(ii) matters relating to quality, continuity and extent of service provided by the licensees;`
  line
  line `(iii) compliance by the licensees with the conditions and requirements of their licence;`
  line
  line `(iv) protection of consumer interest;`
  line
  line `(v) electricity supply and overall standards of performance by utilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (11234)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Constitution of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11234&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, within six months from`
  line `the appointed date, by notification, constitute for the purposes of this Act, a Commission for the State to`
  line `be known as the (name of the State) Electricity Regulatory Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Electricity Regulatory Commission, established by a State Government under`
  line `section 17 of the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) and the enactments`
  line `specified in the Schedule, and functioning as such immediately before the appointed date, shall be the`
  line `State Commission for the purposes of this Act and the Chairperson, Members, Secretary, and officers and`
  line `other employees thereof shall continue to hold office, on the same terms and conditions on which they`
  line `were appointed under those Acts:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Chairperson and other Members of the State Commission appointed, before`
  line `the commencement of this Act, under the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) or under the enactments specified in the Schedule, may, on the recommendations of the Selection Committee`
  line `constituted under sub-section (1) of Section 85, be allowed to opt for the terms and conditions under this`
  line `Act by the concerned State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and`
  line `immovable, and to contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the State Commission shall be at such place as the State Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Commission shall consist of not more than three Members, including the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson and Members of the State Commission shall be appointed by the State`
  line `Government on the recommendation of a Selection Committee referred to in section 85.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (11235)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Joint Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11235&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in section 82, a Joint`
  line `Commission may be constituted by an agreement to be entered into--`
  line
  line `(a) by two or more Governments of States; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the Central Government, in respect of one or more Union territories, and one or more`
  line `Governments of States,`
  line
  line `and shall be in force for such period and shall be subject to renewal for each further period, if any, as may`
  line `be stipulated in the agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Joint Commission, constituted under section 21A of Electricity Regulatory`
  line `Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) and functioning as such immediately before the appointed day, shall`
  line `be the Joint Commission for the purposes of this Act and the Chairperson, Members, Secretary and other`
  line `officers and employees thereof shall be deemed to have been appointed as such under this Act and they`
  line `shall continue to hold office, on the same terms and conditions on which they were appointed under the`
  line `Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998.`
  line
  line `(2) The Joint Commission shall consist of one Member from each of the participating States and`
  line `Union territories and the Chairperson shall be appointed from amongst the Members by consensus, failing`
  line `which by rotation.`
  line
  line `(3) An agreement under sub-section (1) shall contain provisions as to the name of the Joint`
  line `Commission, the manner in which the participating States may be associated in the selection of the`
  line `Chairperson and Members of the Joint Commission, manner of appointment of Members and`
  line `appointment of Chairperson by rotation or consensus, places at which the Commission shall sit,`
  line `apportionment among the participating States of the expenditure in connection with the Joint`
  line `Commission, manner in which the differences of opinion between the Joint Commission and the State`
  line `Government concerned would be resolved and may also contain such other supplemental, incidental and`
  line `consequential provisions not inconsistent with this Act as may be deemed necessary or expedient for`
  line `giving effect to the agreement.`
  line
  line `(4) The Joint Commission shall determine tariff in respect of the participating States or Union`
  line `territories separately and independently.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the Central Government may, if so authorised`
  line `by all the participating States, constitute a Joint Commission and may exercise the powers in respect of all`
  line `or any of the matters specified under sub-section (3) and when so specifically authorised by the`
  line `participating States.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (11236)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and Members of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11236&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson and the Members of the State Commission shall be persons of ability, integrity and standing who have adequate knowledge of, and have shown capacity in, dealing with problems relating to`
  line `engineering, finance, commerce, economics, law or management.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government may appoint any`
  line `person as the Chairperson from amongst persons who is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appointment under this sub-section shall be made except after consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of that High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson or any other Member of the State Commission shall not hold any other office.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson shall be the Chief Executive of the State Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (11237)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Constitution of Selection Committee to select Members of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11237&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall, for the purposes of selecting the Members of the State Commission, constitute a`
  line `Selection Committee consisting of --`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has been a Judge of the High Court. Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Secretary of the concerned State .Member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chairperson of the Authority or the Chairperson of the Central Commission .. Member:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to the appointment of a person as the`
  line `Chairperson who is or has been a Judge of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, within one month from the date of occurrence of any vacancy by`
  line `reason of death, resignation or removal of the Chairperson or a Member and six months before the`
  line `superannuation or end of tenure of the Chairperson or Member, make a reference to the Selection`
  line `Committee for filling up of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Selection Committee shall finalise the selection of the Chairperson and Members within three`
  line `months from the date on which the reference is made to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of two names for every vacancy referred to it.`
  line
  line `(5) Before recommending any person for appointment as the Chairperson or other Member of the`
  line `State Commission, the Selection Committee shall satisfy itself that such person does not have any`
  line `financial or other interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as such Chairperson or`
  line `Member, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) No appointment of Chairperson or other Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any`
  line `vacancy in the Selection Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (11238)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Functions of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11238&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall discharge the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) determine the tariff for generation, supply, transmission and wheeling of electricity,`
  line `wholesale, bulk or retail, as the case may be, within the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that where open access has been permitted to a category of consumers under section 42,`
  line `the State Commission shall determine only the wheeling charges and surcharge thereon, if any, for the`
  line `said category of consumers;`
  line
  line `(b) regulate electricity purchase and procurement process of distribution licensees including the`
  line `price at which electricity shall be procured from the generating companies or licensees or from other`
  line `sources through agreements for purchase of power for distribution and supply within the State;`
  line
  line `(c) facilitate intra-State transmission and wheeling of electricity;`
  line
  line `(d) issue licences to persons seeking to act as transmission licensees, distribution licensees and`
  line `electricity traders with respect to their operations within the State;`
  line
  line `(e) promote cogeneration and generation of electricity from renewable sources of energy by`
  line `providing suitable measures for connectivity with the grid and sale of electricity to any person, and`
  line `also specify, for purchase of electricity from such sources, a percentage of the total consumption of`
  line `electricity in the area of a distribution licensee;`
  line
  line `(f) adjudicate upon the disputes between the licensees and generating companies and to refer any`
  line `dispute for arbitration;`
  line
  line `(g) levy fee for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) specify State Grid Code consistent with the Grid Code specified under clause (h) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(i) specify or enforce standards with respect to quality, continuity and reliability of service by`
  line licensees;
  line
  line `(j) fix the trading margin in the intra-State trading of electricity, if considered, necessary;`
  line
  line `(k) discharge such other functions as may be assigned to it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall advise the State Government on all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) promotion of competition, efficiency and economy in activities of the electricity industry;`
  line
  line `(ii) promotion of investment in electricity industry;`
  line
  line `(iii) reorganisation and restructuring of electricity industry in the State;`
  line
  line `(iv) matters concerning generation, transmission , distribution and trading of electricity or any`
  line `other matter referred to the State Commission by that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Commission shall ensure transparency while exercising its powers and discharging its`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(4) In discharge of its functions, the State Commission shall be guided by the National Electricity`
  line `Policy, National Electricity Plan and tariff policy published under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (11239)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `State Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11239&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission may, by notification, establish with`
  line `effect from such date as it may specify in such notification, a Committee to be known as the State`
  line `Advisory Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Advisory Committee shall consist of not more than twenty-one members to represent`
  line `the interests of commerce, industry, transport, agriculture, labour, consumers, non-governmental`
  line `organisations and academic and research bodies in the electricity sector.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the State Commission shall be the ex officio Chairperson of the State Advisory`
  line `Committee and the Members of the State Commission and the Secretary to State Government in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department dealing with Consumer Affairs and Public Distribution System shall be the`
  line `ex officio Members of the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (11240)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Objects of State Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11240&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the State Advisory Committee shall be to`
  line `advise the Commission on--`
  line
  line `(i) major questions of policy;`
  line
  line `(ii) matters relating to quality, continuity and extent of service provided by the licensees;`
  line
  line `(iii) compliance by licensees with the conditions and requirements of their licence:`
  line
  line `(iv) protection of consumer interest; and`
  line
  line `(v) electricity supply and overall standards of performance by utilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (11241)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11241&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson or other Member`
  line `shall hold office for a term of five years from the date he enters upon his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or other Member in the Central Commission or the State Commission`
  line `shall not be eligible for re-appointment in the same capacity as the Chairperson or a Member in that`
  line `Commission in which he had earlier held office as such:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Chairperson or Member shall hold office as such after he has attained the age`
  line `of sixty-five years.`
  line
  line `(2) The salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and Members`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed by the Appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Members, shall`
  line `not be varied to their disadvantage after appointment.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Member shall, before entering upon his office, make and subscribe to an oath of office and`
  line `secrecy in such form and in such manner and before such authority as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a Member may--=`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing to the Appropriate Government a notice of not less`
  line `than three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 90.`
  line
  line `(5) Any member ceasing to hold office as such shall--`
  line
  line `(a) not accept any commercial employment for a period of two years from the date he ceases to`
  line `hold such office; and`
  line
  line `(b) not represent any person before the Central Commission or any State Commission in any`
  line manner.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section "commercial employment" means employment in`
  line `any capacity in any organisation which has been a party to the proceedings before the Appropriate`
  line `Commission or employment in any capacity under, or agency of, a person engaged in trading,`
  line `commercial, industrial or financial business in electricity industry and includes a director of a company or`
  line `partner of a firm or setting up practice either independently or as partner of a firm or as an advisor or a`
  line consultant.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Andhra Pradesh`
  line
  line `In section 89, in sub-section (1), for the existing two provisos, the following provisos shall be`
  line `substituted, in their application to the State of Andhra Pradesh, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that the Chairperson or other Member in the State Commission shall be eligible for`
  line `re-appointment in the same capacity and shall hold office as such, till he completes the term of five years`
  line `including the term already held before such re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Chairperson or Member shall hold office as such after he attained the age of`
  line `seventy years."`
  line
  line `[Vide Andhra Pradesh Act 11 of 2016, sec. 3 (w.e.f. 14-4-2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (11242)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Removal of Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11242&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Member shall be removed from office except in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Commission, in the case of a Member of the Central Commission, and the State`
  line `Government, in the case of a Member of the State Commission, may by order remove from office any`
  line `Member, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Appropriate Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member;`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a Member;`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line
  line `(f) has been guilty of proved misbehaviour:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member shall be removed from his office on any ground specified in clauses (d), (e)`
  line `and (f) unless the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal on a reference being made to him in this behalf`
  line `by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, has, on an inquiry, held by him`
  line `in accordance with such procedure as may be prescribed by the Central Government, reported that the`
  line `Member ought on such ground or grounds to be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, may, in consultation with`
  line `the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal suspend any Member of the Appropriate Commission in`
  line `respect of whom a reference has been made to the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal, under`
  line `sub-section (2) until the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, has passed`
  line `orders on receipt of the report of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal, on such reference:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to the Chairperson of the Appropriate`
  line `Commission who, at the time of his appointment as such is a sitting Judge of the Supreme Court or the`
  line `Chief Justice of a High Court or a Judge of a High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (11243)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Secretary, officers and other employees of Appropriate Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11243&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate`
  line `Commission may appoint a Secretary to exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be`
  line specified.
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Commission may, with the approval of the Appropriate Government, specify the`
  line `numbers, nature and categories of other officers and employees.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Secretary, officers and other employees shall be such as may be specified with the approval of the`
  line `Appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appropriate Commission may appoint consultants required to assist that Commission in the`
  line `discharge of its functions on the terms and conditions as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (11244)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Proceedings of Appropriate Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11244&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Commission shall meet at the`
  line `head office or any other place at such time as the Chairperson may direct, and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at its meetings) as`
  line `it may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson, or if he is unable to attend a meeting of the Appropriate Commission, any other`
  line `Member nominated by the Chairperson in this behalf and, in the absence of such nomination or where`
  line `there is no Chairperson, any Member chosen by the Members present from amongst themselves, shall`
  line `preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Appropriate Commission shall be decided`
  line `by a majority of votes of the Members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the`
  line `Chairperson or in his absence, the person presiding shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (3), every Member shall have one vote.`
  line
  line `(5) All orders and decisions of the Appropriate Commission shall be authenticated by its Secretary or`
  line `any other officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (11245)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11245&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the Appropriate`
  line `Commission shall be questioned or shall be invalidated merely on the ground of existence of any vacancy`
  line `or defect in the constitution of the Appropriate Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (11246)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Powers of Appropriate Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11246&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Commission shall, for the purposes`
  line `of any inquiry or proceedings under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as evidence;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning of any public record;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commission for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions, directions and orders;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Commission shall have the powers to pass such interim order in any proceeding,`
  line `hearing or matter before the Appropriate Commission, as that Commission may consider appropriate.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appropriate Commission may authorise any person, as it deems fit, to represent the interest of`
  line `the consumers in the proceedings before it.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (11247)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Proceedings before Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11247&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `All proceedings before the Appropriate Commission shall be`
  line `deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) and the Appropriate Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of`
  line `sections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (11248)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Powers of entry and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11248&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission or any officer, not below the rank of`
  line `a Gazetted Officer specially authorised in this behalf by the Commission, may enter any building or place`
  line `where the Commission has reason to believe that any document relating to the subject matter of the`
  line `inquiry may be found, and may seize any such document or take extracts or copies therefrom subject to`
  line `the provisions of section 100 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), in so far as it may be`
  line applicable.
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (11249)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11249&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to`
  line `any Member, Secretary, officer of the Appropriate Commission or any other person subject to such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act`
  line `(except the powers to adjudicate disputes under Section 79 and Section 86 and the powers to make`
  line `regulations under section 178 or section 181) as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (11250)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Grants and loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11250&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament in this behalf, make to the Central Commission grants and loans of`
  line `such sums of money as that Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (11251)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Establishment of Fund by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11251&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be`
  line `called the Central Electricity Regulatory Commission Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) any grants and loans made to the Central Commission by the Central Government under`
  line `section 98;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees received by the Central Commission under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by the Central Commission from such other sources as may be decided upon`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salary, allowances and other remuneration of Chairperson, Members, Secretary, officers`
  line `and other employees of the Central Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses of the Central Commission in discharge of its functions under section 79;`
  line
  line `(c) the expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India,`
  line `prescribe the manner of applying the Fund for meeting the expenses specified in clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (11252)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Accounts and audit of Central Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11252&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Commission shall maintain`
  line `proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Central Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with`
  line `such audit shall be payable by the Central Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Central Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and`
  line `privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `has in connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to`
  line `demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the Central Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Central Commission, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India or any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (11253)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Annual report of Central Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11253&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Commission shall prepare once every`
  line `year, in such form and at such time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a summary of its`
  line `activities during the previous year and copies of the report shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (11254)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Grants and Loans by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11254&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Legislature of a State in this behalf, make to the State Commission grants and loans of such`
  line `sums of money as that Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (11255)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Establishment of Fund by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11255&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be`
  line `called the State Electricity Regulatory Commission fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line `(a) any grants and loans made to the State Commission by the State Government under`
  line `section 102;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees received by the State Commission under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by the State Commission from such other sources as may be decided upon`
  line `by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salary, allowances and other remuneration of Chairperson, Members, Secretary, officers`
  line `and other employees of the State Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses of the State Commission in discharge of its functions under section 86;`
  line
  line `(c) the expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India,`
  line `prescribe the manner of applying the Fund for meeting the expenses specified in clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (11256)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Accounts and audit of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11256&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Accounts of the State Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with`
  line `such audit shall be payable by the State Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the State Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and`
  line `privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `generally has in connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right`
  line `to demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the State Commission, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India or any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the State Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is received, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (11257)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Annual report of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11257&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall prepare once every year`
  line `in such form and at such time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a summary of its activities`
  line `during the previous year and copies of the report shall be forwarded to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (11258)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Budget of Appropriate Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11258&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Commission shall prepare, in such form`
  line `and at such time in each financial year as may be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year,`
  line `showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of that Commission and forward the same to the`
  line `Appropriate Government`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (11259)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11259&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its functions, the Central`
  line `Commission shall be guided by such directions in matters of policy involving public interest as the`
  line `Central Government may give to it in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any such direction relates to a matter of policy involving`
  line `public interest, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (11260)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Directions by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11260&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its functions, the State Commission`
  line `shall be guided by such directions in matters of policy involving public interest as the State Government`
  line `may give to it in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any such direction relates to a matter of policy involving`
  line `public interest, the decision of the State Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (11261)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Directions to Joint Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11261&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where any`
  line `Joint Commission is established under section 83--`
  line
  line `(a) the Government of the State, for which the Joint Commission is established, shall be`
  line `competent to give any direction under this Act only in cases where such direction relates to matter`
  line `within the exclusive territorial jurisdiction of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Government alone shall be competent to give any direction under this Act where`
  line `such direction relates to a matter within the territorial jurisdiction of two or more States or pertaining`
  line `to a Union territory if the participating Governments fail to reach an agreement or the participating`
  line `States or majority of them request the Central Government to issue such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (11262)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Establishment of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 16 and the Schedule, for 'under this Act" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11262&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by notification, establish`
  line `an Appellate Tribunal to be known as the Appellate Tribunal for Electricity to hear appeals against the`
  line `orders of the adjudicating officer or the Appropriate Commission ^1`
  line `[under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force].`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (11263)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11263&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made by an adjudicating`
  line `officer under this Act (except under section 127) or an order made by the Appropriate Commission under`
  line `this Act may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal for Electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person appealing against the order of the adjudicating officer levying any penalty`
  line `shall, while filing the appeal, deposit the amount of such penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where in any particular case, the Appellate Tribunal is of the opinion that the`
  line `deposit of such penalty would cause undue hardship to such person, it may dispense with such deposit`
  line `subject to such conditions as it may deem fit to impose so as to safeguard the realisation of penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer or the Appropriate Commission is received`
  line `by the aggrieved person and it shall be in such form, verified in such manner and be accompanied by such`
  line `fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties`
  line `to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal and`
  line `to the concerned adjudicating officer or the Appropriate Commission, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within one`
  line `hundred and eighty days from the date of receipt of the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any appeal could not be disposed of within the said period of one hundred and`
  line `eighty days, the Appellate Tribunal shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the appeal`
  line `within the said period.`
  line
  line `(6) The Appellate Tribunal may, for the purpose of examining the legality, propriety or correctness of`
  line `any order made by the adjudicating officer or the Appropriate Commission under this Act, as the case`
  line `may be, in relation to any proceeding, on its own motion or otherwise, call for the records of such`
  line `proceedings and make such order in the case as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (11264)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Composition of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11264&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall consist of a Chairperson`
  line `and three other Members.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the Appellate Tribunal may be exercised by Benches thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) a Bench may be constituted by the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal with two or more`
  line `Members of the Appellate Tribunal as the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that every Bench constituted under this clause shall include at least one Judicial`
  line `Member and one Technical Member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Benches of the Appellate Tribunal shall ordinarily sit at Delhi and such other places as the`
  line `Central Government may, in consultation with the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal, notify;`
  line
  line `(d) the Central Government shall notify the areas in relation to which each Bench of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal may exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `may transfer a Member of the Appellate Tribunal from one Bench to another Bench.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(i) "Judicial Member" means a Member of the Appellate Tribunal appointed as such under subclause`
  line `(i) of caluse (b) of sub-section (1) of section 113, and includes the Chairperson of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(ii) "Technical Member" means a Member of the Appellate Tribunal appointed as such under`
  line `sub-clause (ii) or sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) of subsection (1) of section 113.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (11265)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson and Member of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11265&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member`
  line `of the Appellate Tribunal unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal, is, or has been, a judge of the`
  line `Supreme Court or the Chief Justice of a High Court; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Member of the Appellate Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(i) is, or has been, or is qualified to be, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is, or has been, a Secretary for at least one year in the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with economic affairs or matters or infrastructure; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is, or has been, a person of ability and standing, having adequate knowledge or`
  line
  line `experience in dealing with the matters relating to electricity generation, transmission and`
  line `distribution and regulation or economics, commerce, law or management.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal shall be appointed by the Central Government after`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Members of the Appellate Tribunal shall be appointed by the Central Government on the`
  line `recommendation of the Selection Committee referred to in section 78.`
  line
  line `(4) Before appointing any person for appointment as Chairperson or other Member of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, the Central Government shall satisfy itself that such person does not have any financial or other`
  line `interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as such Chairperson or Member.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (11266)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11266&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall hold office as such for a term of three years from the date on which he enters upon his`
  line `office:`
  line
  line `Provided that such Chairperson or other Member shall be eligible for reappointment for a second term`
  line `of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or Member of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall hold office as such after he has attained,`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal, the age of seventy years;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Member of the Appellate Tribunal, the age of sixty-five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (11267)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Terms and conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11267&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms`
  line `and conditions of service of, the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal and Members of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall be varied to his`
  line `disadvantage after appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (11268)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title Vacancies.
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11268&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `If, for reason other than temporary absence, any vacancy occurs in the office of the`
  line `Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal, the Central Government`
  line `shall appoint another person in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill the vacancy and the`
  line `proceedings may be continued before the Appellate Tribunal from the stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (11269)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11269&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign`
  line `his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall,`
  line `unless he is permitted by the Central Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office`
  line `until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as`
  line `his successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal or a Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall not be`
  line `removed from his office except by an order by the Central Government on the ground of proved`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity after an inquiry made by a judge of the Supreme Court, as the Central`
  line `Government may appoint for this purpose in which the Chairperson or a Member of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal concerned has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard in respect of such charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117_a:
  sectionId (49376)
  sectionNo 117A
  orderNo 118
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=49376&sectionno=117A&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_117_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[117A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Member.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of office, salaries`
  line `and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and`
  line `other Members of the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the commencement of ^2[`
  line `the Tribunals Reforms`
  line `Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson and Member appointed before the commencement of Part XIV of`
  line `Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this`
  line `Act, and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had not`
  line `come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_117_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 180 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 25, for “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of the section 184 of that Act” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (11270)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 119
  title `Member to act as Chairperson in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11270&sectionno=118&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of the occurrence of`
  line `any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal by reason of his death, resignation`
  line `or otherwise, the senior-most Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall act as the Chairperson of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal until the date on which a new Chairperson, appointed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal is unable to discharge his functions owing to`
  line `absence, illness or any other cause, the senior-most Member of the Appellate Tribunal shall discharge the`
  line `functions of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal until the date on which the Chairperson of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal resumes his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (11271)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 120
  title `Officers and other employees of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11271&sectionno=119&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `provide the Appellate Tribunal with such officers and other employees as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall discharge their functions under`
  line `the general superintendence of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Appellate Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (11272)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 121
  title `Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11272&sectionno=120&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound`
  line `by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the`
  line `principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `have powers to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1982), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such record or document from`
  line `any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing a representation of default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal or any representation for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made by the Appellate Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal as a decree of civil court and, for this purpose, the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers`
  line `of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if`
  line `it were a decree made by that court.`
  line
  line `(5) All proceedings before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (11273)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 122
  title `Power of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 4, for section 121 (w.e.f. 27-1-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11273&sectionno=121&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[121. Power of Appellate Tribunal.–The Appellate Tribunal may, after hearing the Appropriate`
  line `Commission or other interested party, if any, from time to time, issue such orders, instructions or`
  line `directions as it may deem fit, to any Appropriate Commission for the performance of its statutory`
  line `functions under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (11274)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 123
  title `Distribution of business amongst Benches and transfer of cases from one Bench to another Bench.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11274&sectionno=122&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where Benches are constituted, the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal may, from time totime, by notification, make provisions as to the distribution of the business of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `amongst the Benches and also provide for the matters which may be dealt with by each Bench.`
  line
  line `(2) On the application of any of the parties and after notice to the parties, and after hearing such of`
  line `them as he may desire to be heard, or on his own motion without such notice, the Chairperson of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may transfer any case pending before one Bench, for disposal, to any other Bench.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (11275)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 124
  title `Decision to be by majority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11275&sectionno=123&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `If the Members of the Appellate Tribunal of a Bench consisting of`
  line `two Members differ in opinion on any point, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and`
  line `make a reference to the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal who shall either hear the point or points`
  line `himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or points by one or more of the other Members of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of`
  line `the Members of the Appellate Tribunal who have heard the case, including those who first heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (11276)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 125
  title `Right of appellant to take assistance of legal practitioner and of Appropriate Commission to appoint presenting officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11276&sectionno=124&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person preferring an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under this`
  line `Act may either appear in person or take the assistance of a legal practitioner of his choice to present his`
  line `case before the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Commission may authorise one or more legal practitioners or any of its officers`
  line `to act as presenting officers and every person so authorised may present the case with respect to any`
  line `appeal before the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (11277)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 126
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11277&sectionno=125&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, may, file an appeal to the Supreme Court within sixty days from the date of communication of`
  line `the decision or order of the Appellate Tribunal, to him, on any one or more of the grounds specified in`
  line `section 100 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (11278)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 127
  title Assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11278&sectionno=126&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) If on an inspection of any place or premises or after inspection of the`
  line `equipments, gadgets, machines, devices found connected or used, or after inspection of records`
  line `maintained by any person, the assessing officer comes to the conclusion that such person is indulging in`
  line `unauthorised use of electricity, he shall provisionally assess to the best of his judgment the electricity`
  line `charges payable by such person or by any other person benefited by such use.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of provisional assessment shall be served upon the person in occupation or possession`
  line `or in charge of the place or premises in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) The person, on whom an order has been served under sub-section (2), shall be entitled to file`
  line `objections, if any, against the provisional assessment before the assessing officer, who shall, after`
  line `affording a reasonable opportunity of hearing to such person, pass a final order of assessment within`
  line `thirty days from the date of service of such order of provisional assessment, of the electricity charges`
  line `payable by such person.]`
  line
  line `(4) Any person served with the order of provisional assessment may, accept such assessment and`
  line `deposit the assessed amount with the licensee within seven days of service of such provisional assessment`
  line `order upon him:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(5) If the assessing officer reaches to the conclusion that unauthorised use of electricity has taken`
  line `place, the assessment shall be made for the entire period during which such unauthorised use of electricity`
  line `has taken place and if, however, the period during which such unauthorised use of electricity has taken`
  line `place cannot be ascertained, such period shall be limited to a period of twelve months immediately`
  line `preceding the date of inspection.]`
  line
  line `(6) The assessment under this section shall be made at a rate equal to ^4`
  line `[twice] the tariff rates`
  line `applicable for the relevant category of services specified in sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "assessing officer" means an officer of a State Government or Board or licensee, as the case`
  line `may be, designated as such by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "unauthorised use of electricity" means the usage of electricity--`
  line
  line `(i) by any artificial means; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by a means not authorised by the concerned person or authority or licensee; or`
  line
  line `(iii) through a tampered meter; or`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(iv) for the purpose other than for which the usage of electricity was authorised; or`
  line
  line `(v) for the premises or areas other than those for which the supply of electricity was`
  line authorised.]
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 11, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 26 of 2007, s. 11 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "one-and-half times" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub-clause (iv) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (11279)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 128
  title `Appeal to Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "one-third of the assessed amount" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11279&sectionno=127&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by the final order made under`
  line `section 126 may, within thirty days of the said order, prefer an appeal in such form, verified in such`
  line `manner and be accompanied by such fee as may be specified by the State Commission, to an appellate`
  line `authority as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal against an order of assessment under sub-section (1) shall be entertained unless an`
  line `amount equal to^1`
  line `[half of the assessed amount] is deposited in cash or by way of bank draft with the`
  line `licensee and documentary evidence of such deposit has been enclosed along with the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) The appellate authority referred to in sub-section (1) shall dispose of the appeal after hearing the`
  line `parties and pass appropriate order and send copy of the order to the assessing officer and the appellant.`
  line
  line `(4) The order of the appellate authority referred to in sub-section (1) passed under sub-section (3)`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) No appeal shall lie to the appellate authority referred to in sub-section (1) against the final order`
  line `made with the consent of the parties.`
  line
  line `(6) When a person defaults in making payment of assessed amount, he, in addition to the assessed`
  line `amount shall be liable to pay, on the expiry of thirty days from the date of order of assessment, an amount`
  line `of interest at the rate of sixteen per cent. per annum compounded every six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (11280)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 129
  title `Investigation of certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11280&sectionno=128&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Commission may, on being satisfied that`
  line `a licensee has failed to comply with any of the conditions of licence or a generating company or a`
  line `licensee has failed to comply with any of the provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made`
  line `thereunder, at any time, by order in writing, direct any person (hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `Investigating Authority) specified in the order to investigate the affairs of any generating company or`
  line `licensee and to report to that Commission on any investigation made by such Investigating Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Investigating Authority may, wherever necessary, employ any auditor or any other`
  line `person for the purpose of assisting him in any investigation under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in section 235 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), the Investigating Authority may, at any time, and shall, on being directed so to do by the`
  line `Appropriate Commission, cause an inspection to be made, by one or more of its officers, of any licensee`
  line `or generating company and his books of account; and the Investigating Authority shall supply to the`
  line `licensee or generating company, as the case may be, a copy of his report on such inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of every manager, managing director or other officer of the licensee or`
  line `generating company, as the case may be, to produce before the Investigating Authority directed to make`
  line `the investigation under sub-section (1), or inspection under sub-section (2), all such books of account,`
  line `registers and other documents in his custody or power and to furnish him with any statement and`
  line `information relating to the affairs of the licensee or generating company, as the case may be, as the said`
  line `Investigating Authority may require of him within such time as the said Investigating Authority may`
  line specify.
  line
  line `(4) Any Investigating Authority, directed to make an investigation under sub-section (1), or`
  line `inspection under sub-section (2), may examine on oath any manager, managing director or other officer of`
  line `the licensee or generating company, as the case may be, in relation to his business and may administer`
  line `oaths accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) The Investigating Authority, shall, if it has been directed by the Appropriate Commission to`
  line `cause an inspection to be made, and may, in any other case, report to the Appropriate Commission on any`
  line `inspection made under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of any report under sub-section (1) or sub-section (5), the Appropriate Commission`
  line `may, after giving such opportunity to the licensee or generating company, as the case may be, to make a`
  line `representation in connection with the report as in the opinion of the Appropriate Commission seems`
  line `reasonable, by order in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) require the licensee or the generating company to take such action in respect of any matter`
  line `arising out of the report as the Appropriate Commission may think fit; or`
  line
  line `(b) cancel the licence; or`
  line
  line `(c) direct the generating company to cease to carry on the business of generation of electricity.`
  line
  line `(7) The Appropriate Commission may, after giving reasonable notice to the licensee or the generating`
  line `company, as the case may be, publish the report submitted by the Investigating Authority under`
  line `sub-section (5) or such portion thereof as may appear to it to be necessary.`
  line
  line `(8) The Appropriate Commission may specify the minimum information to be maintained by the`
  line `licensee or the generating company in their books, the manner in which such information shall be`
  line `maintained, the checks and other verifications to be adopted by licensee or the generating company in thatconnection and all other matters incidental thereto as are, in its opinion, necessary to enable the`
  line `Investigating Authority to discharge satisfactorily its functions under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression licensee or the generating company`
  line `shall include in the case of a licensee incorporated in India--`
  line
  line `(a) all its subsidiaries formed for the purpose of carrying on the business of generation or`
  line `transmission or distribution or trading of electricity exclusively outside India; and`
  line
  line `(b) all its branches whether situated in India or outside India.`
  line
  line `(9) All expenses of, and incidental to, any investigation made under this section shall be defrayed by`
  line `the licensee or the generating company, as the case may be, and shall have priority over the debts due`
  line `from the licensee or the generating company and shall be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (11281)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 130
  title `Orders for securing compliance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11281&sectionno=129&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Appropriate Commission, on the basis of`
  line `material in its possession, is satisfied that a licensee is contravening, or is likely to contravene, any of the`
  line `conditions mentioned in his licence or conditions for grant of exemption or the licensee or the generating`
  line `company has contravened or is likely to contravene any of the provisions of this Act, it shall, by an order,`
  line `give such directions as may be necessary for the purpose of securing compliance with that condition or`
  line provision.
  line
  line `(2) While giving direction under sub-section (1), the Appropriate Commission shall have due regard`
  line `to the extent to which any person is likely to sustain loss or damage due to such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (11282)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 131
  title `Procedure for issuing directions by Appropriate Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11282&sectionno=130&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate`
  line `Commission, before issuing any direction under section 129, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) serve notice in the manner as may be specified to the concerned licensee or the generating`
  line company;
  line
  line `(b) publish the notice in the manner as may be specified for the purpose of bringing the matters to`
  line `the attention of persons, likely to be affected, or affected;`
  line
  line `(c) consider suggestions and objections from the concerned licensee or generating company and`
  line `the persons, likely to be affected, or affected.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (11283)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 132
  title `Vesting of property of Board in State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11283&sectionno=131&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from the date on which a`
  line `transfer scheme, prepared by the State Government to give effect to the objects and purposes of this Act,`
  line `is published or such further date as may be stipulated by the State Government (hereafter in this Part`
  line `referred to as the effective date), any property, interest in property, rights and liabilities which`
  line `immediately before the effective date belonged to the State Electricity Board (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the Board) shall vest in the State Government on such terms as may be agreed between the State`
  line `Government and the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Any property, interest in property, rights and liabilities vested in the State Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be re-vested by the State Government in a Government company or in a company or`
  line `companies, in accordance with the transfer scheme so published along with such other property, interest`
  line `in property, rights and liabilities of the State Government as may be stipulated in such scheme, on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be agreed between the State Government and such company or companies`
  line `being State Transmission Utility or generating company or transmission licensee or distribution licensee,`
  line `as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the transfer value of any assets transferred hereunder shall be determined, as far as may`
  line `be, based on the revenue potential of such assets at such terms and conditions as may be agreed between the State Government and the State Transmission Utility or generating company or transmission licensee`
  line `or distribution licensee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where,--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer scheme involves the transfer of any property or rights to any person or`
  line `undertaking not wholly owned by the State Government, the scheme shall give effect to the transfer`
  line `only for fair value to be paid by the transferee to the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) a transaction of any description is effected in pursuance of a transfer scheme, it shall be`
  line `binding on all persons including third parties and even if such persons or third parties have not`
  line `consented to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, after consulting the Government company or company or companies`
  line `being State Transmission Utility or generating company or transmission licensee or distribution licensee,`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) (hereinafter referred to as the transferor), require such transferor to draw up`
  line `a transfer scheme to vest in a transferee being any other generating company or transmission licensee or`
  line `distribution licensee, the property, interest in property, rights and liabilities which have been vested in the`
  line `transferor under this section, and publish such scheme as statutory transfer scheme under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) A transfer scheme under this section may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the formation of subsidiaries, joint venture companies or other schemes of`
  line `division, amalgamation, merger, reconstruction or arrangements which shall promote the profitability`
  line `and viability of the resulting entity, ensure economic efficiency, encourage competition and protect`
  line `consumer interests;`
  line
  line `(b) define the property, interest in property, rights and liabilities to be allocated--`
  line
  line `(i) by specifying or describing the property, rights and liabilities in question; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by referring to all the property, interest in property, rights and liabilities comprised in a`
  line `described part of the transferor's undertaking; or`
  line
  line `(iii) partly in one way and partly in the other;`
  line
  line `(c) provide that any rights or liabilities stipulated or described in the scheme shall be enforceable`
  line `by or against the transferor or the transferee;`
  line
  line `(d) impose on the transferor an obligation to enter into such written agreements with or execute`
  line `such other instruments in favour of any other subsequent transferee as may be stipulated in the`
  line scheme;
  line
  line `(e) mention the functions and duties of the transferee;`
  line
  line `(f) make such supplemental, incidental and consequential provisions as the transferor considers`
  line `appropriate including provision stipulating the order as taking effect; and`
  line
  line `(g) provide that the transfer shall be provisional for a stipulated period.`
  line
  line `(6) All debts and obligations incurred, all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to`
  line `be done by the Board, with the Board or for the Board, or the State Transmission Utility or generating`
  line `company or transmission licensee or distribution licensee, before a transfer scheme becomes effective`
  line `shall, to the extent specified in the relevant transfer scheme, be deemed to have been incurred, entered`
  line `into or done by the Board, with the Board or for the State Government or the transferee and all suits or`
  line `other legal proceedings instituted by or against the Board or transferor, as the case may be, may be`
  line `continued or instituted by or against the State Government or concerned transferee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) The Board shall cease to be charged with and shall not perform the functions and duties with`
  line `regard to transfers made on and after the effective date.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this Part,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Government company" means a Government Company formed and registered under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(b) "company" means a company to be formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956) to undertake generation or transmission or distribution in accordance with the scheme`
  line `under this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (11284)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 133
  title `Use of proceeds of sale or transfer of Board, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11284&sectionno=132&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `In the event that a Board or any utility`
  line `owned or controlled by the Appropriate Government is sold or transferred in any manner to a person who`
  line `is not owned or controlled by the Appropriate Government, the proceeds from such sale or transfer shall`
  line `be utilised in priority to all other dues in the following order, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) dues (including retirement benefits due) to the officers and employees of such Board or utility,`
  line `who have been affected by the aforesaid sale or transfer;`
  line
  line `(b) payment of debt or other liabilities of the transferor as may be required by the existing loan`
  line covenants.
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (11285)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 134
  title `Provisions relating to officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11285&sectionno=133&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by a transfer`
  line `scheme, provide for the transfer of the officers and employees to the transferee on the vesting of`
  line `properties, rights and liabilities in such transferee as provided under section 131.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon such transfer under the transfer scheme, the personnel shall hold office or service under the`
  line `transferee on such terms and conditions as may be determined in accordance with the transfer scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that such terms and conditions on the transfer shall not in any way be less favourable than`
  line `those which would have been applicable to them if there had been no such transfer under the transfer`
  line `scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the transfer can be provisional for a stipulated period.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and the transfer scheme, the expression "officers and`
  line `employees" shall mean all officers and employees who on the date specified in the scheme are the officers`
  line `and employees of the Board or transferor, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (11286)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 135
  title `Payment of compensation or damages on transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11286&sectionno=134&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or any other law for the time being in force and except for`
  line `the provisions made in this Act, the transfer of the employment of the officers and employees referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) of section 133 shall not entitle such officers and employees to any compensation or`
  line `damages under this Act, or any other Central or State law, save as provided in the transfer scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (11287)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 136
  title `Theft of Electricity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11287&sectionno=135&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line ^26
  line `[(1) Whoever, dishonestly,--`
  line
  line `(a) taps, makes or causes to be made any connection with overhead, underground or under water`
  line `lines or cables, or service wires, or service facilities of a licensee or supplier, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) tampers a meter, installs or uses a tampered meter, current reversing transformer, loop`
  line `connection or any other device or method which interferes with accurate or proper registration,`
  line `calibration or metering of electric current or otherwise results in a manner whereby electricity is`
  line `stolen or wasted; or`
  line
  line `(c) damages or destroys an electric meter, apparatus, equipment, or wire or causes or allows any`
  line `of them to be so damaged or destroyed as to interfere with the proper or accurate metering of`
  line `electricity; or`
  line
  line `(d) uses electricity through a tampered meter; or`
  line
  line `(e) uses electricity for the purpose other than for which the usage of electricity was authorised,`
  line
  line `so as to abstract or consume or use electricity shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three years or with fine or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where the load abstracted, consumed, or used or attempted abstraction or`
  line `attempted consumption or attempted use--`
  line
  line `(i) does not exceed 10 kilowatt, the fine imposed on first conviction shall not be less than`
  line `three times the financial gain on account of such theft of electricity and in the event of second or`
  line `subsequent conviction the fine imposed shall not be less than six times the financial gain on`
  line `account of such theft of electricity;`
  line
  line `(ii) exceeds 10 kilowatt, the fine imposed on first conviction shall not be less than three times`
  line `the financial gain on account of such theft of electricity and in the event of second or subsequent`
  line `conviction, the sentence shall be imprisonment for a term not less than six months, but which may`
  line `extend to five years and with fine not less than six times the financial gain on account of such`
  line `theft of electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the event of second and subsequent conviction of a person where the load`
  line `abstracted, consumed, or used or attempted abstraction or attempted consumption or attempted use`
  line `exceeds 10 kilowatt, such person shall also be debarred from getting any supply of electricity for a`
  line `period which shall not be less than three months but may extend to two years and shall also be`
  line `debarred from getting supply of electricity for that period from any other source or generating station:`
  line
  line `Provided also that if it is proved that any artificial means or means not authorised by the Board or`
  line `licensee or supplier, as the case may be, exist for the abstraction, consumption or use of electricity by`
  line `the consumer, it shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, that any abstraction, consumption or`
  line `use of electricity has been dishonestly caused by such consumer.`
  line
  line `(1A) Without prejudice to the provisions of this Act, the licensee or supplier, as the case may be,`
  line `may, upon detection of such theft of electricity, immediately disconnect the supply of electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided that only such officer of the licensee or supplier, as authorised for the purpose by the`
  line `Appropriate Commission or any other officer of the licensee or supplier, as the case may be, of the`
  line `rank higher than the rank so authorised shall disconnect the supply line of electricity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such officer of the licensee or supplier, as the case may be, shall lodge a`
  line `complaint in writing relating to the commission of such offence in police station having jurisdiction`
  line `within twenty-four hours from the time of such disconnection:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the licensee or supplier, as the case may be, on deposit or payment of the`
  line `assessed amount or electricity charges in accordance with the provisions of this Act, shall, without`
  line `prejudice to the obligation to lodge the complaint as referred to in the second proviso to this clause,`
  line `restore the supply line of electricity within forty-eight hours of such deposit or payment.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^2`
  line `[Any officer of the licensee or supplier as the case may be, authorised] in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter, inspect, break open and search any place or premises in which he has reason to believe that`
  line `electricity ^3`
  line `[has been or is being], used unauthorisedly;`
  line
  line `(b) search, seize and remove all such devices, instruments, wires and any other facilitator or`
  line `article which 1`
  line `has been, or is being, used for unauthorised use of electricity;`
  line
  line `(c) examine or seize any books of account or documents which in his opinion shall be useful for`
  line `or relevant to, any proceedings in respect of the offence under sub-section (1) and allow the person`
  line `from whose custody such books of account or documents are seized to make copies thereof or take`
  line `extracts therefrom in his presence.`
  line
  line `(3) The occupant of the place of search or any person on his behalf shall remain present during the`
  line `search and a list of all things seized in the course of such search shall be prepared and delivered to such`
  line `occupant or person who shall sign the list:`
  line
  line `Provided that no inspection, search and seizure of any domestic places or domestic premises shall be`
  line `carried out between sunset and sunrise except in the presence of an adult male member occupying such`
  line premises.
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to search and seizure`
  line `shall apply, as far as may be, to searches and seizure under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 13, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 13, for "Any officer authorised" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 5, for "has been, is being, or is likely to be," (w.e.f. 27-1-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (11288)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 137
  title `Theft of electric lines and materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11288&sectionno=136&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, dishonestly--`
  line
  line `(a) cuts or removes or takes way or transfers any electric line, material or meter from a tower,`
  line `pole, any other installation or place of installation or any other place, or site where it may be`
  line `rightfully or lawfully stored, deposited, kept, stocked, situated or located including during`
  line `transportation, without the consent of the licensee or the owner, as the case may be, whether or not`
  line `the act is done for profit or gain; or`
  line
  line `(b) stores, possesses or otherwise keeps in his premises, custody or control, any electric line,`
  line `material or meter without the consent of the owner, whether or not the act is committed for profit or`
  line `gain; or`
  line
  line `(c) loads, carries, or moves from one place to another any electric line, material or meter without`
  line `the consent of its owner, whether or not the act is done for profit or gain,`
  line
  line `is said to have committed an offence of theft of electric lines and materials, and shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person, having been convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1) is again guilty`
  line `of an offence punishable under that sub-section, he shall be punishable for the second or subsequent`
  line `offence for a term of imprisonment which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to five`
  line `years and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (11289)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 138
  title `Punishment for receiving stolen property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11289&sectionno=137&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, dishonestly receives any stolen electric`
  line `line or material knowing or having reasons to believe the same to be stolen property, shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years or with fine or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (11290)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 139
  title `Interference with meters or works of licensee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11290&sectionno=138&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever,--`
  line
  line `(a) unauthorisedly connects any meter, indicator or apparatus with any electric line through which`
  line `electricity is supplied by a licensee or disconnects the same from any such electric line; or`
  line
  line `(b) unauthorisedly reconnects any meter, indicator or apparatus with any electric line or other`
  line `works being the property of a licensee when the said electric line or other works has or have been cut`
  line `or disconnected; or`
  line
  line `(c) lays or causes to be laid, or connects up any works for the purpose of communicating with any`
  line `other works belonging to a licensee; or.`
  line
  line `(d) maliciously injures any meter, indicator, or apparatus belonging to a licensee or wilfully or`
  line `fraudulently alters the index of any such meter, indicator or apparatus or prevents any such meter,`
  line `indicator or apparatus from duly registering,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both, and, in the case of a continuing offence, with a daily fine`
  line `which may extend to five hundred rupees; and if it is proved that any means exist for making such`
  line `connection as is referred to in clause (a) or such re-connection as is referred to in clause (b), or such`
  line `communication as is referred to in clause (c), for causing such alteration or prevention as is referred to in`
  line `clause (d), and that the meter, indicator or apparatus is under the custody or control of the consumer,`
  line `whether it is his property or not, it shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, that such connection,`
  line `reconnection, communication, alteration, prevention or improper use, as the case may be, has been`
  line `knowingly and wilfully caused by such consumer.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (11291)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 140
  title `Negligently breaking or damaging works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 6, for sections 139 and 140 (w.e.f. 27-4-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11291&sectionno=139&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[139. Negligently breaking or damaging works.--Whoever, negligently breaks, injures, throws`
  line `down or damages any material connected with the supply of electricity, shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to ten thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (11292)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 141
  title `Penalty for intentionally injuring works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 6, for sections 139 and 140 (w.e.f. 27-1-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11292&sectionno=140&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `^1[Whoever, with intent to cut off the supply of`
  line `electricity, cuts or injures, or attempts to cut or injure, any electric supply line or works, shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (11293)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 142
  title `Extinguishing public lamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11293&sectionno=141&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, maliciously extinguishes any public lamp shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (11294)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 143
  title `Punishment for non-compliance of directions by Appropriate Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11294&sectionno=142&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `In case any`
  line `complaint is filed before the Appropriate Commission by any person or if that Commission is satisfied`
  line `that any person has contravened any of the provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made`
  line `thereunder, or any direction issued by the Commission, the Appropriate Commission may after giving`
  line `such person an opportunity of being heard in the matter, by order in writing, direct that, without prejudice`
  line `to any other penalty to which he may be liable under this Act, such person shall pay, by way of penalty,`
  line `which shall not exceed one lakh rupees for each contravention and in case of a continuing failure with an`
  line `additional penalty which may extend to six thousand rupees for every day during which the failure`
  line `continues after contravention of the first such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (11295)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 144
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11295&sectionno=143&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of adjudging under this Act, the Appropriate`
  line `Commission shall appoint any of its Members to be an adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Appropriate Government, after giving any person concerned a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard for the purpose of imposing any penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding an inquiry, the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or`
  line `produce any document which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to`
  line `the subject-matter of the inquiry, and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has failed to`
  line `comply with the provisions of section 29 or section 33 or section 43, he may impose such penalty as he`
  line `thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of any of those sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (11296)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 145
  title `Factors to be taken into account by adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11296&sectionno=144&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `While adjudicating the quantum of`
  line `penalty under section 29 or section 33 or section 43, the adjudicating officer shall have due regard to the`
  line `following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of disproportionate gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a`
  line `result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the repetitive nature of the default.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (11297)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 146
  title `Civil courts not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11297&sectionno=145&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit`
  line `or proceeding in respect of any matter which an assessing officer referred to in section 126 or an appellate`
  line `authority referred to in section 127 or the adjudicating officer appointed under this Act is empowered by`
  line `or under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect`
  line `of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (11298)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 147
  title `Punishment for non-compliance of orders or directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 2003, s. 7 (w.e.f. 27-1-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11298&sectionno=146&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fails to comply with any`
  line `order or direction given under this Act, within such time as may be specified in the said order or direction`
  line `or contravenes or attempts or abets the contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or any rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `months or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both in respect of each offence and in`
  line `the case of a continuing failure, with an additional fine which may extend to five thousand rupees for`
  line `every day during which the failure continues after conviction of the first such offence:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to the orders, instructions or directions`
  line `issued under section 121.]`
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (11299)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 148
  title `Penalties not to affect other liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11299&sectionno=147&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `The penalties imposed under this Act shall be in`
  line `addition to, and not in derogation of, any liability in respect of payment of compensation or, in the case of`
  line `a licensee, the revocation of his licence which the offender may have incurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (11300)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 149
  title `Penalty where works belong to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11300&sectionno=148&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall, so far as they`
  line `are applicable, be deemed to apply also when the acts made punishable thereunder are committed in the`
  line `case of electricity supplied by or of works belonging to the Appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (11301)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 150
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11301&sectionno=149&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of and was responsible`
  line `to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of having committed the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of having committed such offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (11302)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 151
  title Abetment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11302&sectionno=150&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever abets an offence punishable under this Act, shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), be punished with the punishment provided for`
  line `the offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to any penalty or fine which may be imposed or prosecution proceeding which`
  line `may be initiated under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, if any officer or other`
  line `employee of the Board or the licensee enters into or acquiesces in any agreement to do, abstains from`
  line `doing, permits, conceals or connives at any act or thing whereby any theft of electricity is committed, he`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of section 135, sub-section (1) of section`
  line `136, section 137 and section 138, the licence or certificate of competency or permit or such other`
  line `authorisation issued under the rules made or deemed to have been made under this Act to any person who`
  line `acting as an electrical contractor, supervisor or worker abets the commission of an offence punishable`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 135, sub-section (1) of section 136, section 137, or section 138, on his`
  line `conviction for such abetment, may also be cancelled by the licensing authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of such cancellation shall be made without giving such person an opportunity`
  line `of being heard.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "licencing authority" means the officer who for the`
  line `time being in force is issuing or renewing such licence or certificate of competency or permit or such`
  line `other authorisation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (11303)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 152
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s.15, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11303&sectionno=151&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act`
  line `except upon a complaint in writing made by the Appropriate Government or Appropriate Commission or`
  line `any of their officer authorised by them or a Chief Electrical Inspector or an Electrical Inspector or`
  line `licensee or the generating company, as the case may be, for this purpose.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the court may also take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act upon a`
  line `report of a police officer filed under section 173 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided further that a special court constituted under section 153 shall be competent to take`
  line `cognizance of an offence without the accused being committed to it for trial.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Substitution of section 151.--For section 151 of the Electricity Act, 2003 (Central Act 36 of 2003),`
  line `the following shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"151. Institution of prosecution.--No prosecution, shall be instituted against may person for any`
  line `offence under this Act or any rule, regulation, licence or order made or issued there under, except at the`
  line `instance of the State Government or a licencee or a generating company under the Act or an officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the State Government or a licencee or a generating company or by any person`
  line `affected by the act alleged to constitute the offence."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 12 of 2006, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Substitution of section 151 of Act 36 of 2003.---For section 151 of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003), in`
  line `its application to the State of Maharashtra (hereinafter referred to as "the principal Act"), the following section shall`
  line `be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"151. Cognizance of offences.--No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act`
  line except,--
  line
  line `(a) upon a complaint in writing made by Appropriate Government or Appropriate Commission or any of`
  line `their officer authorised by them or a Chief Electrical Inspector or an Electrical Inspector or a licensee or the`
  line `generating company, as the case may be, for this purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) upon a police report of facts which constitute an offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that, such police report is based on the First Information Report filed a person who is authorised to file`
  line `a complaint under clause (a).`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 36 of 2005, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_151_a:
  sectionId (11304)
  sectionNo 151A
  orderNo 153
  title `Power of police to investigate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s.16, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11304&sectionno=151A&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_151_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[151A. Power of police to investigate.--For the purposes of investigation of an offence punishable`
  line `under this Act, the police officer shall have all the powers as provided in Chapter XII of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_151_b:
  sectionId (11305)
  sectionNo 151B
  orderNo 154
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s.16, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11305&sectionno=151B&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_151_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[151B. Certain offences to be cognizable and non-bailable.--Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under sections 135 to 140 or`
  line `section 150 shall be cognizable and non-bailable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (11306)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 155
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11306&sectionno=152&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Appropriate Government or any officer authorised by it in this behalf`
  line `may accept from any consumer or person who committed or who is reasonably suspected of having`
  line `committed an offence of theft of electricity punishable under this Act, a sum of money by way ofcompounding of the offence as specified in the Table below:`
  line
  line TABLE
  line
  line `Nature of Service Rate at which the sum of money for compounding to be collected per`
  line `Kilowatt (KW)/Horse Power (HP) or part thereof for Low Tension`
  line `(LT) supply and per Kilo Volt Ampere (KVA) of contracted demand`
  line `for High Tension (HT)`
  line
  line `(1) (2)`
  line `1. Industrial Service twenty thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `2. Commercial Service ten thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `3. Agricultural Service two thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `4. Other Services four thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the`
  line `rates specified in the Table above.`
  line
  line `(2) On payment of the sum of money in accordance with sub-section (1), any person in custody in`
  line `connection with that offence shall be set at liberty and no proceedings shall be instituted or continued`
  line `against such consumer or person in any criminal court.`
  line
  line `(3) The acceptance of the sum of money for compounding an offence in accordance with`
  line `sub-section (1) by the Appropriate Government or an officer empowered in this behalf shall be deemed to`
  line `amount to an acquittal within the meaning of section 300 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974).`
  line
  line `(4) The compounding of an offence under sub-section (1) shall be allowed only once for any person`
  line `or consumer.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (11307)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 156
  title `Constitution of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 17, for "sections 135 to 139" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11307&sectionno=153&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, for the purposes of providing`
  line `speedy trial of offences referred to in ^1[sections 135 to 140 and section 150], by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute as many Special Courts as may be necessary for such area or areas, as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of a single Judge who shall be appointed by the State Government`
  line `with the concurrence of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judge of a Special Court unless he was,`
  line `immediately before such appointment, an Additional District and Sessions Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the office of the Judge of a Special Court is vacant, or such Judge is absent from the`
  line `ordinary place of sitting of such Special Court, or he is incapacitated by illness or otherwise for the`
  line `performance of his duties, any urgent business in the Special Court shall be disposed of--`
  line
  line `(a) by a Judge, if any, exercising jurisdiction in the Special Court;`
  line
  line `(b) where there is no such other Judge available, in accordance with the direction of District and`
  line `Sessions Judge having jurisdiction over the ordinary place of sitting of Special Court, as notified`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 153 of Act (36 of 2003).--In section 153 of the principal Act, after sub-section (4), the`
  line `following sub-section shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) Where no Special Court for any area or areas has been constituted under sub-section (1), one or more`
  line `Additional District and Sessions Judges, as may be designated by the High Court, for such area or areas, from time`
  line `to time, shall exercise the powers of the Special Court under this Act and any Judge so designated shall be deemed`
  line `to be a special Court for the purposes of this Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 36 of 2005, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (11308)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 157
  title `Procedure and power of Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11308&sectionno=154&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every offence punishable under ^1`
  line `[sections 135 to 140 and`
  line `section 150] shall be triable only by the Special Court within whose jurisdiction such offence has been`
  line committed.
  line
  line `(2) Where it appears to any court in the course of any inquiry or trial that an offence punishable under`
  line `^1[sections 135 to 140 and section 150] in respect of any offence that the case is one which is triable by a`
  line `Special Court constituted under this Act for the area in which such case has arisen, it shall transfer such`
  line `case to such Special Court, and thereupon such case shall be tried and disposed of by such Special Court`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for such Special Court to act on the evidence, if any, recorded by any`
  line `court in the case of presence of the accused before the transfer of the case to any Special Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such Special Court is of opinion that further examination, cross-examination`
  line `and re-examination of any of the witnesses whose evidence has already been recorded, is required in the`
  line `interest of justice, it may re-summon any such witness and after such further examination, crossexamination`
  line `or re-examination, if any, as it may permit, the witness shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(3) The Special Court may, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of section 260 or`
  line `section 262 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), try the offence referred to in ^1[sections`
  line `135 to 140 and section 150] in a summary way in accordance with the procedure prescribed in the said`
  line `Code and the provisions of sections 263 to 265 of the said Code shall, so far as may be, apply to such`
  line `trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in the course of a summary trial under this subsection, it appears to the Special`
  line `Court that the nature of the case is such that it is undesirable to try such case in summary way, the Special`
  line `Court shall recall any witness who may have been examined and proceed to re-hear the case in the`
  line `manner provided by the provisions of the said Code for the trial of such offence:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be`
  line `lawful for a Special Court to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding five years.`
  line
  line `(4) A Special Court may, with a view to obtaining the evidence of any person supposed to have been`
  line `directly or indirectly concerned in or privy to, any offence tender pardon to such person on condition of`
  line `his making a full and true disclosure of the circumstances within his knowledge relating to the offence`
  line `and to every other person concerned whether as principal or abettor in the commission thereof, and any`
  line `pardon so tendered shall, for the purposes of section 308 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), be deemed to have been tendered under section 307 thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) The ^2[Special Court shall] determine the civil liability against a consumer or a person in terms of`
  line `money for theft of energy which shall not be less than an amount equivalent to two times of the tariff rate`
  line `applicable for a period of twelve months preceding the date of detection of theft of energy or the exact`
  line `period of theft if determined whichever is less and the amount of civil liability so determined shall be`
  line `recovered as if it were a decree of civil court.`
  line
  line `(6) In case the civil liability so determined finally by the Special Court is less than the amount`
  line `deposited by the consumer or the person, the excess amount so deposited by the consumer or the person,`
  line `to the Board or licensee or the concerned person, as the case may be, shall be refunded by the Board or licensee or the concerned person, as the case may be, within a fortnight from the date of communication`
  line `of the order of the Special Court together with interest at the prevailing Reserve Bank of India prime`
  line `lending rate for the period from the date of such deposit till the date of payment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "civil liability" means loss or damage incurred by the`
  line `Board or licensee or the concerned person, as the case may be, due to the commission of an offence`
  line `referred to in ^3[sections 135 to 140 and section 150.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 154 of Act 36 of 2003.--In section 154 of the principal Act, for sub-section (1),`
  line `the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) every Special Court may take cognizance of an offence without the accused being committed to it`
  line `for trial; and`
  line
  line `(b) every offence punishable under sections 135 to 139 shall be triable only by the Special Court`
  line `within whose jurisdiction such offence has been committed."`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 36 of 2005, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 18 for "sections 135 to 139" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "Special Court may" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s.18, for "sections 135 to 139" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (11309)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 158
  title `Special Court to have powers of Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11309&sectionno=155&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act, shall apply to the proceedings before the Special Court and for the purpose of the provisions of`
  line `the said enactments, the Special Court shall be deemed to be a Court of Session and shall have all powers`
  line `of a Court of Session and the person conducting a prosecution before the Special Court shall be deemed to`
  line `be a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (11310)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 159
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11310&sectionno=156&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the powers`
  line `conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), as if the`
  line `Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court is a District Court, or as the case`
  line `may be, the Court of Session, trying cases within the local limits of jurisdiction of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (11311)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 160
  title Review.
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11311&sectionno=157&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `The Special Court may, on a petition or otherwise and in order to prevent miscarriage`
  line `of justice, review its judgment or order passed under section 154, but no such review petition shall be`
  line `entertained except on the ground that it was such order passed under a mistake of fact, ignorance of any`
  line `material fact or any error apparent on the face of the record:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Special Court shall not allow any review petition and set aside its previous order or`
  line `judgment without hearing the parties affected.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Part, "Special Courts" means the Special Courts constituted`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 153.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (11312)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 161
  title Arbitration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11312&sectionno=158&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Where any matter is, by or under this Act, directed to be determined by arbitration,`
  line `the matter shall, unless it is otherwise expressly provided in the licence of a licensee, be determined by`
  line `such person or persons as the Appropriate Commission may nominate in that behalf on the application of`
  line `either party; but in all other respects the arbitration shall be subject to the provisions of the Arbitration`
  line `and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (11313)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 162
  title `Protection of railways, highways, airports and canals, docks, wharfs and piers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11313&sectionno=159&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall, in the generation, transmission, distribution, supply or use of electricity, in any way injure any`
  line `railway, highway, airports, tramway, canal or water-way or any dock, wharf or pier vested in or`
  line `controlled by a local authority, or obstruct or interfere with the traffic on any railway, airway, tramway,`
  line `canal or water-way.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (11314)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 163
  title `Protection of telegraphic, telephonic and electric signalling lines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11314&sectionno=160&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person`
  line `generating, transmitting, distributing, supplying or using electricity (hereinafter in this section referred to`
  line `as the "operator") shall take all reasonable precautions in constructing, laying down and placing his`
  line `electric lines, electrical plant and other works and in working his system, so as not injuriously to affect,`
  line `whether by induction or otherwise, the working of any wire or line used for the purpose of telegraphic,`
  line `telephone or electric signalling communication, or the currents in such wire or line.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any difference or dispute arises between the operator, and the telegraph authority as to`
  line `whether the operator has constructed, laid down or placed his electric lines, electrical plant or other`
  line `works, or worked his system, in contravention of sub-section (1), or as to whether the working of any`
  line `wire, line or current is or is not injuriously affected thereby, the matter shall be referred to the Central`
  line `Government and the Central Government, unless it is of opinion that the wire or line has been placed in`
  line `unreasonable proximity to the electric lines, electrical plant or works of the operator after the construction`
  line `of such lines, plant or works, may direct the operator to make such alterations in, or additions to, his`
  line `system as may be necessary in order to comply with the provisions of this section, and the operator shall`
  line `make such alterations or additions accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the repair, renewal or amendment of any`
  line `electric line or electrical plant so long as the course of the electric line or electrical plant and the amount`
  line `and nature of the electricity transmitted thereby are not altered.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the operator makes default in complying with the requirements of this section, he shall`
  line `make full compensation for any loss or damage incurred by reason thereof, and, where any difference or`
  line `dispute arises as to the amount of such compensation, the matter shall be determined by arbitration.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a telegraph line shall be deemed to be injuriously`
  line `affected if telegraphic, telephonic or electric signalling communication by means of such line is, whether`
  line `through induction or otherwise, prejudicially interfered with by an electric line, electrical plant or other`
  line `work or by any use made thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (11315)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 164
  title `Notice of accidents and injuries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11315&sectionno=161&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any accident occurs in connection with the generation,`
  line `transmission, distribution, supply or use of electricity in or in connection with, any part of the electric`
  line `lines or electrical plant of any person and the accident results or is likely to have resulted in loss of human`
  line `or animal life or in any injury to a human being or an animal, such person shall give notice of the`
  line `occurrence and of any such loss or injury actually caused by the accident, in such form and within such`
  line `time as may be prescribed, to the Electrical Inspector or such other person as aforesaid and to such other`
  line `authorities as the Appropriate Government may by general or special order, direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Government may, if it thinks fit, require any Electrical Inspector, or any other`
  line `person appointed by it in this behalf, to inquire and report--`
  line
  line `(a) as to the cause of any accident affecting the safety of the public, which may have been`
  line `occasioned by or in connection with, the generation, transmission, distribution, supply or use of`
  line `electricity, or`
  line
  line `(b) as to the manner in, and extent to, which the provisions of this Act or rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder or of any licence, so far as those provisions affect the safety of any person, have`
  line `been complied with.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Electrical Inspector or other person holding an inquiry under sub-section (2) shall have all`
  line `the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the purpose of`
  line `enforcing the attendance of witnesses and compelling the production of documents and material objects,`
  line `and every person required by an Electrical Inspector be legally bound to do so within the meaning of`
  line `section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (11316)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 165
  title `Appointment of Chief Electrical Inspector and Electrical Inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11316&sectionno=162&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint duly qualified persons to be Chief Electrical Inspector or`
  line `Electrical Inspectors and every such Inspector so appointed shall exercise the powers and perform the`
  line `functions of a Chief Electrical Inspector or an Electrical Inspector under this Act and exercise such other`
  line `powers and perform such other functions as may be prescribed within such areas or in respect of such`
  line `class of works and electric installations and subject to such restrictions as the Appropriate Government`
  line `may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of express provision to the contrary in this Act, or any rule made thereunder, an`
  line `appeal shall lie from the decision of a Chief Electrical Inspector or an Electrical Inspector to the`
  line `Appropriate Government or if the Appropriate Government, by general or special order so directs, to an`
  line `Appropriate Commission.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 162.--In section 162 of the Principal Act, after sub-section (2), the`
  line `following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(3) where no provision is made by Central Government or the Authority in respect of powers`
  line `and functions and qualifications of Chief Electrical Inspector and Electrical Inspectors, the State`
  line `Government may by rules prescribe the same".`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 39 of 2014, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (11317)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 166
  title `Power for licensee to enter premises and to remove fittings or other apparatus of licensee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11317&sectionno=163&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) A licensee or any person duly authorised by a licence may, at any reasonable time, and on informing`
  line `the occupier of his intention, enter any premises to which electricity is, or has been, supplied by him, of`
  line `any premises or land, under, over, along, across, in or upon which the electric supply-lines or other works`
  line `have been lawfully placed by him for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(a) inspecting, testing, repairing or altering the electric supply-lines, meters, fittings, works and`
  line `apparatus for the supply of electricity belonging to the licensee; or`
  line
  line `(b) ascertaining the amount of electricity supplied or the electrical quantity contained in the`
  line `supply; or`
  line
  line `(c) removing where a supply of electricity is no longer required, or where the licensee is`
  line `authorised to take away and cut off such supply, any electric supply-lines, meters, fittings, works or`
  line `apparatus belonging to the licensee.`
  line
  line `(2) A licensee or any person authorised as aforesaid may also, in pursuance of a special order in this`
  line `behalf made by an Executive Magistrate and after giving not less than twenty-four hours notice in writing`
  line `to the occupier,--`
  line
  line `(a) enter any premises or land referred to in sub-section (1) for any of the purposes mentioned`
  line therein;
  line
  line `(b) enter any premises to which electricity is to be supplied by him, for the purpose of examining`
  line `and testing the electric wires fittings, works and apparatus for the use of electricity belonging to the`
  line consumer.
  line
  line `(3) Where a consumer refuses to allow a licensee or any person authorised as aforesaid to enter his`
  line `premises or land in pursuance of the provisions of sub-section (1) or, sub-section (2), when such licensee`
  line `or person has so entered, refuses to allow him to perform any act which he is authorised by those`
  line `sub-sections to perform, or fails to give reasonable facilities for such entry or performance, the licensee`
  line `may, after the expiry of twenty-four hours from the service of a notice in writing on the consumer, cut off`
  line `the supply to the consumer for so long as such refusal or failure continues, but for no longer.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (11318)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 167
  title `Exercise of powers of Telegraph Authority in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11318&sectionno=164&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `The Appropriate Government`
  line `may, by order in writing, for the placing of electric lines or electrical plant for the transmission of`
  line `electricity or for the purpose of telephonic or telegraphic communications necessary for the proper coordination`
  line `of works, confer upon any public officer, licensee or any other person engaged in the business`
  line `of supplying electricity under this Act, subject to such conditions and restrictions, if any, as the`
  line `Appropriate Government may think fit to impose and to the provisions of the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885`
  line `(13 of 1885), any of the powers which the telegraph authority possesses under that Act with respect to the`
  line `placing of telegraph lines and posts for the purposes of a telegraph established or maintained, by the`
  line `Government or to be so established or maintained.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (11319)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 168
  title `Amendment of sections 40 and 41 of Act 1 of 1894.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11319&sectionno=165&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) In section 40, sub-section (1) of clause`
  line `(b) and section 41, sub-section (5) of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894, the term "work" shall be deemed to`
  line `include electricity supplied or to be supplied by means of the work to be constructed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appropriate Government may, on recommendation of the Appropriate Commission in this`
  line `behalf, if it thinks fit, on the application of any person, not being a company desirous of obtaining any`
  line `land for its purposes, direct that he may acquire such land under the provisions of the Land Acquisition`
  line `Act, 1894 (1 of 1894) in the same manner and on the same conditions as it might be acquired if the person`
  line `were a company.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (11320)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 169
  title `Coordination forum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11320&sectionno=166&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall constitute a coordination forum`
  line `consisting of the Chairperson of the Central Commission and Members thereof, the Chairperson of the`
  line `Authority, representatives of generating companies and transmission licensees engaged in inter-State`
  line `transmission of electricity for smooth and coordinated development of the power system in the country.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall also constitute a forum of regulators consisting of the Chairperson`
  line `of the Central Commission and Chairpersons of the State Commissions.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the Central Commission shall be the Chairperson of the Forum of regulators`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall constitute a Coordination Forum consisting of the Chairperson of the`
  line `State Commission and Members thereof representatives of the generating companies, transmission`
  line `licensee and distribution licensees engaged in generation, transmission and distribution of electricity in`
  line `that State for smooth and coordinated development of the power system in the State.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be a committee in each district to be constituted by the Appropriate Government--`
  line
  line `(a) to coordinate and review the extension of electrification in each district;`
  line
  line `(b) to review the quality of power supply and consumer satisfaction;`
  line
  line `(c) to promote energy efficiency and its conservation.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (11321)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 170
  title `Exemption of electric lines or electrical plants from attachment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11321&sectionno=167&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `Where any`
  line `electric lines or electrical plant, belonging to a licensee are placed in or upon any premises or land not`
  line `being in the possession of the licensee, such electric lines or electrical plant shall not be liable to be taken`
  line `in execution under any process of any civil court or in any proceedings in insolvency against the person in`
  line `whose possession the same may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (11322)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 171
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11322&sectionno=168&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Appropriate Government or Appellate Tribunal or the Appropriate Commission or any officer`
  line `of Appropriate Government, or any Member, Officer or other employee of the Appellate Tribunal or any`
  line `Members, officer or other employees of the Appropriate Commission or the assessing officer or any`
  line `public servant for anything done or in good faith purporting to be done under this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (11323)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 172
  title `Members, officers, etc., of Appellate Tribunal, Appropriate Commission to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11323&sectionno=169&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the Appellate Tribunal and the`
  line `Chairperson, Members, Secretary, officers and other employees of the Appropriate Commission and the`
  line `assessing officer referred to in section 126 shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance`
  line `of any of the provisions of this Act to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (11324)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 173
  title `Recovery of penalty payable under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11324&sectionno=170&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `Any penalty payable by a person under this Act,`
  line `if not paid, may be recovered as if it were an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (11325)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 174
  title `Services of notices, orders or documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11325&sectionno=171&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, order or document by or under this`
  line `Act required, or authorised to be addressed to any person may be served on him by delivering the same`
  line `after obtaining signed acknowledgement receipt therefor or by registered post or such means of delivery`
  line `as may be prescribed--`
  line
  line `(a) where the Appropriate Government is the addressee, at the office of such officer as the`
  line `Appropriate Government may prescribe in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) where the Appropriate Commission is the addressee, at the office of the Appropriate`
  line Commission;
  line
  line `(c) where a company is the addressee, at the registered office of the company or, in the event of`
  line `the registered office of the company not being in India, at the head office of the company in India;`
  line
  line `(d) where any other person is the addressee, at the usual or last known place of abode or business`
  line `of the person.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notice, order or document by or under this Act required or authorised to be addressed to the`
  line `owner or occupier of any premises shall be deemed to be properly addressed if addressed by the`
  line `description of the owner or occupier of the premises (naming the premises), and may be served by`
  line `delivering it, or a true copy thereof, to some person on the premises, or if there is no person on the`
  line `premises to whom the same can with reasonable diligence be delivered, by affixing it on some`
  line `conspicuous part of the premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (11326)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 175
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11326&sectionno=172&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) a State Electricity Board constituted under the repealed laws shall be deemed to be the State`
  line `Transmission Utility and a licensee under the provisions of this Act for a period of one year from the`
  line `appointed date or such earlier date as the State Government may notify, and shall perform the duties`
  line `and functions of the State Transmission Utility and a licensee in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and rules and regulations made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by notification, authorise the State Electricity Board to`
  line `continue to function as the State Transmission Utility or a licensee for such further period beyond the`
  line `said period of one year as may be mutually decided by the Central Government and the State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) all licences, authorisations, approvals, clearances and permissions granted under the`
  line `provisions of the repealed laws may, for a period not exceeding one year from the appointed date or`
  line `such earlier period, as may be notified by the Appropriate Government, continue to operate as if the`
  line `repealed laws were in force with respect to such licences, authorisations, approvals, clearances and`
  line `permissions, as the case may be, and thereafter such licences, authorisations, approvals, clearances`
  line `and permissions shall be deemed to be licences, authorisations, approvals, clearances and permission`
  line `under this Act and all provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly to such licences, authorisations,`
  line `approvals, clearances and permissions;`
  line
  line `(c) the undertaking of the State Electricity Boards established under section 5 of the Electricity`
  line `(Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948) may after the expiry of the period specified in clause (a) be`
  line `transferred in accordance with the provisions of Part XIII of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the State Government may, by notification, declare that any or all the provisions contained in`
  line `this Act, shall not apply in that State for such period, not exceeding six months from the appointed`
  line `date, as may be stipulated in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (11327)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 176
  title `Inconsistency in laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11327&sectionno=173&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder`
  line `or any instrument having effect by virtue of this Act, rule or regulation shall have effect in so far as it is`
  line `inconsistent with any other provisions of the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) or the Atomic`
  line `Energy Act, 1962 (33 of 1962) or the Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (11328)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 177
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11328&sectionno=174&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in section 173, the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (11329)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 178
  title `Provisions of this Act to be in addition to and not in derogation of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11329&sectionno=175&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of this Act are in addition to and not in derogation of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (11330)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 179
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2007, s. 19, for "(including the capital adequacy, creditworthiness or code of conduct)" (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11330&sectionno=176&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which the objection and suggestions on the draft National Electricity Plan to`
  line `be invited by the Authority under the proviso to sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the additional requirements ^1`
  line `[relating to the capital adequacy, creditworthiness or code of`
  line `conduct] under sixth proviso to section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) the payment of fees for application for grant of licence under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the constitution and functions of the National Load Despatch Centre under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(e) the works of licensees affecting the property of owner or occupier under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 67;`
  line
  line `(f) such other cases which may be prescribed under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(g) allowances and fees payable to others Members for attending the meetings of Authority under`
  line `sub-section (14) of section 70.`
  line
  line `(h) other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and Members of the Authority under`
  line `sub-section (15) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(i) the functions and duties of the Central Electricity Authority under section 73;`
  line
  line `(j) the salary, allowances and other conditions of service of Chairperson and Member of Central`
  line `Commission under sub-section (2) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and manner in which and the authority before whom oath of office and secrecy`
  line `should be subscribed under sub-section (3) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(l) the procedure to be prescribed by the Central Government under the proviso to sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 90;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter required to be prescribed under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 94;`
  line
  line `(n) the form in which the Central Commission shall prepare its annual statement of accounts`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 100;`
  line
  line `(o) the form in which and time at which the Central Commission shall prepare its annual report`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 101;`
  line
  line `(p) the form in which and time at which the Central Commission shall prepare its budget under`
  line `section 106;`
  line
  line `(q) the form and the manner of verifying such form, and fee for filing appeal under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 111;`
  line
  line `(r) the salary and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal and Members of the Appellate Tribunal under section 115;`
  line
  line `(s) the salary and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and employees of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 119;`
  line
  line `(t) the additional matters in respect of which the Appellate Tribunal may exercise the powers of a`
  line `civil court under clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 120;`
  line
  line `(u) the authority to whom the appeal shall be filed under sub-section (1) of section 127;`
  line
  line `(v) manner of holding inquiry by an adjudicating officer under sub-section (1) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(w) the form in which and the time at which service of notices to any person or to the Central`
  line `Government for the purpose under sub-section (1) of section 161;`
  line
  line `(x) the powers to be exercised and the functions to be performed by the Inspectors under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 162;`
  line
  line `(y) the manner of delivery of every notice, order or document to be served under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 171;`
  line
  line `(z) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (11331)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 180
  title `Powers of Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11331&sectionno=177&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, by notification, make`
  line `regulations consistent with this Act and the rules generally to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the power conferred in sub-section (1),`
  line `such regulations may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Grid Standards under section 34;`
  line
  line `(b) suitable measures relating to safety and electric supply under section 53;`
  line
  line `(c) the installation and operation of meters under section 55;`
  line
  line `(d) the rules of procedure for transaction of business under sub-section (9) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(e) the technical standards for construction of electrical plants and electric lines and connectivity`
  line `to the grid under clause (b) of section 73;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and manner in which and the time at which the State Government and licensees shall`
  line `furnish statistics, returns or other information under section 74;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be, specified.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made by the Authority under this Act shall be subject to the conditions of previous`
  line publication.
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (11332)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 181
  title `Powers of Central Commission to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11332&sectionno=178&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Commission may, by`
  line `notification make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules generally to carry out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the power contained in sub-section (1),`
  line `such regulations may provide for all or any of following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) period to be specified under the first proviso to section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and the manner of the application under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner and particulars of notice under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of licence under section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner and particulars of notice under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(f) publication of alterations or amendments to be made in the licence under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(g) Grid Code under sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(h) levy and collection of fees and charge from generating companies or transmission utilities or`
  line `licensees under sub-section (4) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(i) rates, charges and terms and conditions in respect of intervening transmission facilities under proviso to section 36;`
  line
  line `(j) payment of the transmission charges and a surcharge under sub-clause (ii) of clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(k) reduction ^1*** of surcharge and cross subsidies under second proviso to sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(l) payment of transmission charges and a surcharge under sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of`
  line `section 40;`
  line
  line `(m) reduction ^1*** of surcharge and cross-subsidies under the second proviso to sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `clause (c) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(n) proportion of revenues from other business to be utilised for reducing the transmission and`
  line `wheeling charges under proviso to section 41;`
  line
  line `(o) duties of electricity trader under sub-section (2) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(p) standards of performance of a licensee or class of licensees under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 57;`
  line
  line `(q) the period within which information to be furnished by the licensee under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 59;`
  line
  line `^2[(r) the manner of reduction of cross-subsidies under clause (g) of section 61;]`
  line
  line `(s) the terms and conditions for the determination of tariff under section 61;`
  line
  line `(t) details to be furnished by licensee or generating company under sub-section (2) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(u) the procedures for calculating the expected revenue from tariff and charges under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner of making an application before the Central Commission and the fee payable therefor under sub-section (1) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner of publication of application under sub-section (2) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(x) issue of tariff order with modifications or conditions under sub-section (3) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(y) the manner by which development of market in power including trading specified under`
  line `section 66;`
  line
  line `(z) the powers and duties of the Secretary of the Central Commission under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 91;`
  line
  line `(za) the terms and conditions of service of the Secretary, officers and other employees of Central`
  line `Commission under sub-section (3) of section 91;`
  line
  line `(zb) the rules of procedure for transaction of business under sub-section (1) of section 92;`
  line
  line `(zc) minimum information to be maintained by a licensee or the generating company and the`
  line `manner of such information to be maintained under sub-section (8) of section 128;`
  line
  line `(zd) the manner of service and publication of notice under section 130;`
  line
  line `(ze) any other matter which is to be, or may be, specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made by the Central Commission under this Act shall be subject to the conditions`
  line `of previous publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and elimination" omitted by Act 26 of 2007, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for clause (r) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (11333)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 182
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11333&sectionno=179&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government, every regulation made by the Authority, and every regulation made by the Central`
  line `Commission shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of the Parliament, while`
  line `it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line regulation.
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (11334)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 183
  title `Powers of State Governments to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11334&sectionno=180&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the payment of fees for application for grant of licence under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(b) the works of licensees affecting the property of other persons under sub-section (2) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(c) such other matters which may be prescribed under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(d) the salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and`
  line `Members of the State Commission under sub-section (2) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which and the authority before whom oath of office and secrecy should be subscribed under sub-section (3) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter required to be prescribed by the State Commission under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 94;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of applying the Fund under sub-section (3) of section 103;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which and time at which the State Commission shall prepare its annual accounts`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 104;`
  line
  line `(i) the form in which and time at which the State Commission shall prepare its annual report`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 105;`
  line
  line `(j) the form in which and time at which the State Commission shall prepare its budget under`
  line `section 106;`
  line
  line `(k) manner of service of provisional order of assessment under sub-section (2) of section 126;`
  line
  line `(l) manner of holding inquiry by an adjudicating officer under sub-section (1) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(m) the form in which and the time at which notice to the Electrical Inspector under sub-section (1) of section 161;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of delivery of every notice, order or document under sub-section (1) of section 171; and`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 180.--In section 180 of the Principal Act, in sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(a) after clause (a), the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(aa) Subject to section 53,--`
  line
  line `(i) regarding procedure of Inspection by the Chief Electrical Inspector and Electrical`
  line Inspectors;
  line
  line `(ii) regarding terms and conditions and manner of issue of Licence to electrical Contractors,`
  line `permit to Supervisors and Wireman and Competency certificates;`
  line
  line `(iii) manner of Scrutiny and approval of Electrical Installation drawings;`
  line
  line `(iv) Levy of fee for inspections and other services rendered by the Chief Electrical Inspector`
  line `and Electrical Inspectors;`
  line
  line `(v) manner of Collection of fee and if not remitted within the stipulated time to recover the`
  line `same as arrears of land revenue."`
  line
  line `(b) after clause (m), the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(mm) Subject to section 162 regarding powers and functions and qualifications of the Chief`
  line `Electrical Inspector and Electrical Inspectors."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 39 of 2014, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (11335)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 184
  title `Powers of State Commissions to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11335&sectionno=181&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commissions may, by`
  line `notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules generally to carry out the provisions`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the power contained in sub-section (1), such regulations may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) period to be specified under the first proviso to section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and the manner of application under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner and particulars of application for licence to be published under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of licence section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner and particulars of notice under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(f) publication of the alterations or amendments to be made in the licence under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(g) levy and collection of fees and charges from generating companies or licensees under sub-section (3) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(h) rates, charges and the terms and conditions in respect of intervening transmission facilities`
  line `under proviso to section 36;`
  line
  line `(i) payment of the transmission charges and a surcharge under sub-clause (ii) of clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(j) reduction ^1*** of surcharge and cross subsidies under second proviso to sub-clause (ii) of clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(k) manner and utilisation of payment and surcharge under the fourth proviso to sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(l) payment of the transmission charges and a surcharge under sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(m) reduction ^1*** of surcharge and cross subsidies under second proviso to sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of payment of surcharge under the fourth proviso to sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(o) proportion of revenues from other business to be utilised for reducing the transmission and`
  line `wheeling charges under proviso to section 41;`
  line
  line `(p) reduction ^1*** of surcharge and cross-subsidies under the third proviso to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 42;`
  line
  line `(q) payment of additional charges on charges of wheeling under sub-section (4) of section 42;`
  line `(r) guidelines under sub-section (5) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(s) the time and manner for settlement of grievances under sub-section (7) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(t) the period to be specified by the State Commission for the purposes specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(u) methods and principles by which charges for electricity shall be fixed under sub-section (2) of section 45;`
  line
  line `(v) reasonable security payable to the distribution licensee under sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(w) payment of interest on security under sub-section (4) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(x) electricity supply code under section 50;`
  line
  line `(y) the proportion of revenues from other business to be utilised for reducing wheeling charges`
  line `under proviso to section 51;`
  line
  line `(z) duties of electricity trader under sub-section (2) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(za) standards of performance of a licensee or a class of licensees under sub-section (1) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(zb) the period within which information to be furnished by the licensee under sub-section (1) of section 59;`
  line
  line `^2[(zc) the manner of reduction of cross-subsidies under clause (g) of section 61;]`
  line
  line `(zd) the terms and conditions for the determination of tariff under section 61;`
  line
  line `(ze) details to be furnished by licensee or generating company under sub-section (2) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(zf) the methodologies and procedures for calculating the expected revenue from tariff and charges under sub-section (5) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(zg) the manner of making an application before the State Commission and the fee payable therefor under sub-section (1) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(zh) issue of tariff order with modifications or conditions under sub-section (3) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(zi) the manner by which development of market in power including trading specified under section 66;`
  line
  line `(zj) the powers and duties of the Secretary of the State Commission under sub-section (1) of section 91;`
  line
  line `(zk) the terms and conditions of service of the secretary, officers and other employees of the State Commission under sub-section (2) of section 91;`
  line
  line `(zl) rules of procedure for transaction of business under sub-section (1) of section 92;`
  line
  line `(zm) minimum information to be maintained by a licensee or the generating company and the`
  line `manner of such information to be maintained under sub-section (8) of section 128;`
  line
  line `(zn) the manner of service and publication of notice under section 130;`
  line
  line `(zo) the form of preferring the appeal and the manner in which such form shall be verified and the fee for preferring the appeal under sub-section (1) of section 127;`
  line
  line `(zp) any other matter which is to be, or may be, specified.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made by the State Commission under this Act shall be subject to the condition of previous publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and elimination" omitted by Act 26 of 2007, s. 21 (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for clause (zc) (w.e.f. 15-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (11336)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 185
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before State Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11336&sectionno=182&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the State`
  line `Government and every regulation made by the State Commission shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (11337)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 186
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11337&sectionno=183&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (11338)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 187
  title `Provisions of Act not apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11338&sectionno=184&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall not apply to`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with Defence, Atomic Energy or such`
  line `other similar Ministries or Departments or undertakings or Boards or institutions under the control of such`
  line `Ministries or Departments as may be notified by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (11339)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 188
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930&sectionId=11339&sectionno=185&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00001_200336_1517807317930
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Indian Electricity Act, 1910 (9 of 1910), the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948) and the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 998) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken including any rule,`
  line `notification, inspection, order or notice made or issued or any appointment, confirmation or`
  line `declaration made or any licence, permission, authorisation or exemption granted or any document or`
  line `instrument executed or any direction given under the repealed laws shall, in so far as it is not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the provisions contained in sections 12 to 18 of the Indian Electricity Act, 1910 (9 of 1910)`
  line `and rules made thereunder shall have effect until the rules under section 67 to 69 of this Act are made;`
  line
  line `(c) the Indian Electricity Rules, 1956 made under section 37 of the Indian Electricity Act, 1910`
  line `(9 of 1910) as it stood before such repeal shall continue to be in force till the regulations under section`
  line `53 of this Act are made;`
  line
  line `(d) all rules made under sub-section (1) of section 69 of the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948) shall continue to have effect until such rules are rescinded or modified, as the case may`
  line be;
  line
  line `(e) all directives issued, before the commencement of this Act, by a State Government under the`
  line `enactments specified in the Schedule shall continue to apply for the period for which such directions`
  line `were issued by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the enactments specified in the Schedule, not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act, shall apply to the States in which such enactments are applicable.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, as and when considered necessary, by notification, amend the`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), the mention of particular matters in that section,`
  line `shall not be held to prejudice or affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act,`
  line `1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to the effect of repeals.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
